Description: Trigger error when --TRT is not present in custom interventions dataset

Error Message: --TERM is not present in custom events dataset
Description: Trigger error when --TERM is not present in custom events dataset

Description: Trigger error when --LLOQ is not expressed using the units in --STRESU

Description: Trigger error when ARMCD is populated for a subject who was not assigned to treatment

Description: Trigger error when RACE does not equal "MULTIPLE" when multiple races collected and primary race not specified

Description: Trigger error when there is more than one record per subject per EPOCH

Description: Trigger error when MIDSTYPE=TM.MIDSTYPE and TM.TMRPT=Y and MIDS is not suffixed with a sequence number in consistent chronological order

Description: Trigger error when --ORREF is not in the same units as --ORRES

Description: When --STREFC is populated, --STREFN should also be populated.

Description: Trigger error when --STREFN is not in the same units as --STRESN

Description: Trigger error when parameter is non-normalized and terminology for PPORRESU is not for a non-normalized parameter

Error Message: Parameter is normalized by dose amount and terminology for PPORRESU is not for a parameter normalized by dose amount
Description: Trigger error when parameter is normalized by dose amount and terminology for PPORRESU is not for a parameter normalized by dose amount

Error Message: Parameter is normalized by weight and terminology for PPORRESU is not for a parameter normalized by weight
Description: Trigger error when parameter is normalized by weight and terminology for PPORRESU is not for a parameter normalized by weight

Error Message: Parameter is non-normalized and terminology of PPSTRESU is not for a non-normalized parameter
Description: Trigger error when parameter is non-normalized and terminology of PPSTRESU is not for a non-normalized parameter

Error Message: Parameter is normalized by dose amount and terminology of PPSTRESU is not a parameter normalized by dose amount
Description: Trigger error when parameter is normalized by dose amount and terminology of PPSTRESU is not a parameter normalized by dose amount

Error Message: Parameter is normalized by weight and terminology for PPSTRESU is not for a parameter not normalized by weight
Description: Trigger error when parameter is normalized by weight and terminology for PPSTRESU is not for a parameter not normalized by weight

Error Message: --REPNUM is null or is not unique per subject per test per timing variables.
Description: Raise an error when REPNUM is in the dataset and there are multiple records for a subject for a test within the timeframe identified by the timing variables on the record, and --REPNUM is null or not unique per subject per test per timing variables.

Error Message: Record is derived in a data collection tool and RSDRVFL is not equal to "Y"
Description: Raise an error when record is derived in a data collection tool and RSDRVFL is not equal to "Y"
Verify that for finding collected in a \"Other, specify\" CRF field a related parent record exist

Error Message: -OBJ does not equal --DECOD of the parent record
Description: Raise an error when parent record exists and DECOD ^= null, and --OBJ does not equal --DECOD

Error Message: Test targets an organism, group of organisms, or antigen, but MBTEST is not the name of the  organism/antigen.
Description: Verify MBTEST equals the name of the organism/antigen targeted by the identification assay.

Error Message: Test targets an organism, group of organisms, or antigen, but MBTSTDTL is not "DETECTION"
Description: Verify MBTSTDTL is "DETECTION" if the tests targets an organism, group of organisms, or antigen.

Error Message: Test targets an organism, group of organisms, or antigen, but
Description: Verify MBTESTCD is "MCORGIDN" if the test is for a non-targeted identification of organisms.

Error Message: Test is for culture characteristics, but MBTEST is not the name of the  organism or group of organisms.
Description: If the test is for culture characteristics, verify that MBTEST equals the name of the  organism/antigen being characterized.

Error Message: Associated Persons non-supplemental qualifier dataset associated with a split dataset does not have a dataset name with a length greater than 4 and less than, or equal to, 6.
Description: When an Associated Persons non-supplemental qualifier dataset is associated with a split dataset, the dataset name length must be greater than 4 and less than, or equal to, 6.

Rule Type: Variable Metadata Check against Define XML
Error Message: Variable is missing, where variable core status is permissible and data is planned to be collected.
Description: Raise an error when variable Core Status = Permissible and data is planned to be collected, but variable is not present

Error Message: AP Core Domain does not have a value length of 4 characters beginning with 'AP' and ending with 2 character SDTM domain
Description: Raise an error when an AP Core Domain does not have a value length of 4 characters beginning with 'AP' and ending with 2 character SDTM domain

Error Message: --BLFL value must either be "Y" or null
Description: Raise an error when --BLFL value is not populated with either "Y" or null
Raise an error when MADTC or MIDTC or TFDTC is not null and not equal to the date/time of the subject disposition from DS domain

Error Message: AGETXT must be in number dash number format
Description: AGETXT must be in number dash number format

Error Message: AGETXT is populated, so neither BRTHDTC nor AGE may be populated
Description: AGETXT is used to present the age range in situations where the exact birthdate is not known.  If AGETXT is included both BRTHDTC and AGE should not be populated.

Error Message: AGE or AGETXT is populated, but AGEU is not populated
Description: AGEU is the until associated with AGE or AGETXT.  If either of those variables is populated, AGEU should be populated.

Error Message: SPECIES in not present in DM and there is no record TSPARMCD=SPECIES in TS and there is no record TXPARMCD=SPECIES in TX
Description: Raise an error when the variable SPECIES is not oresent in DM, and there is no record TSPARMCD=SPECIES in TS and there is no record TXPARMCD=SPECIES in TX

Error Message: ARMCD is present in TA.ARMCD but is not provided in DM.ARMCD
Description: When study does not use multi-stage arm assignments and ARMCD is populated, ARMCD must be present in TA.ARMCD. This rule has been executed to identify all cases when ARMCD is not present in TA.ARMCD and therefore acknowledges that false positives may be recorded when multi-stage arm assignments are in use.

Error Message: USUBJID is not found in DM.USUBJID
Description: Trigger error when USUBJID is not present in DM in DM.USUBJID

Error Message: SETCD is not present in TX.SETCD
Description: The value of SETCD in DM must be one of the SETCD values in TX.

Error Message: IDVARVAL may not be populated as IDVAR is null
Description: IDVAR must be specified.

Error Message: IDVAR does not represent a variable present in the dataset identified in RDOMAIN
Description: When IDVAR and IDVARVAL are populated those referenced values must exist in the parent domain identified in RDOMAIN.

Error Message: ELEMENT variable has a non-null value when ETCD has a value of 'UNPLAN'
Description: Verify that ELEMENT value is blank when ETCD is equal to UNPLAN

Error Message: SEUPDES variable has a null value when ETCD has a value of 'UNPLAN'
Description: Verify that SEUPDES is populated when ETCD is equal to UNPLAN

Error Message: SESEQ is not chronologically (based on SESTDTC) within USUBJID
Description: Trigger error when the order of SESEQ is not chronologically (based on SESTDTC) within USUBJID

Error Message: SESEQ is not chronologically (based on SESTDTC) within USUBJID
Description: Trigger error when the order of SESEQ is not chronologically (based on SESTDTC) within USUBJID

Error Message: When POOLID is populated, USUBJID may not be populated
Description: Raise an error when both USUBJID and POOLID are empty

Error Message: EXDOSE is 0, EXLOT may not be populated
Description: If no test article (as described in EXTRT) is administered (i.e., EXDOSE is 0), EXLOT is null.

Error Message: --SEQ is not unique within USUBJID or POOLID
Description: Sequence number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.

Error Message: POOLID is not found in POOLDEF.POOLID
Description: Trigger error when POOLID is not present in POOLDEF in DM.USUBJID

Error Message: --STAT does not contain a value from the (ND) codelist
Description: Trigger error when --STAT is non-empty and does not contain a value from the ND codelist

Error Message: When --ORRES is populated, --STAT may not be populated.
Description: Trigger error when --ORRES is populated and --STAT is populated

Error Message: When --STAT is not populated, --REASND may not be populated.
Description: Trigger error when --STAT is not populated and --REASND is populated

Error Message: --BLFL value must either be 'Y' or null
Description: Trigger error when --BLFL is populated and the value is different from "Y"

Error Message: --EXFL value must either be 'Y' or null
Description: Trigger error when --EXFL is populated and the value is different from "Y"

Error Message: --REASEX may only be present when --EXCLFL is 'Y'
Description: Trigger error when --REASEX is populated and --EXCLFL is not 'Y'

Error Message: The Body Weight Gain test is not unique for this subject and date/time.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular Body Weight Gain test, in the BG Domain, for a subject on a particular date.

Error Message: BGSTRESU is not consistent within BGTESTCD
Description: Trigger error when --BGSTRESU is not consistent within BGTESTCD

Error Message: The Clinical Observation test result is not unique for this subject and date/time.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular Result or Findings as Collected, in the CL Domain, for a subject or pool on a particular date.

Error Message: CLRESCAT may not be equal to CLTEST and CLRESCAT may not be equal to CLSCAT
Description: Trigger error when CLRESCAT is equal to CLTEST or when CLRESCAT is equal to CLSCAT

Error Message: The Clinical Observation test result is not unique for this subject and date/time.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular Result or Findings as Collected, in the CL Domain, for a subject or pool on a particular date.

Error Message: --TESTCD > 8 chars
Description: Raise an error when --TESTCD > 8 chars

Error Message: --DRVFL must be null or 'Y'
Description: Raise an error when record is derived in a --DRVFL is not null and is not equal to 'Y'

Error Message: The Macroscopy Finding test result is not unique for this subject and date/time.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular Macroscopic Finding in the MA Domain, for a subject on a particular date.

Error Message: When MATEST is 'Gross Pathological Examination' then MASPEC is required.
Description: When MATEST is "Gross Pathological Examination" MASPEC is required.

Error Message: When MATEST is 'Clinical Signs Follow-up' MASPEC may not be populated.
Description: When MATEST is 'Clinical Signs Follow-up' MASPEC should not be used.

Error Message: --TESTCD may not start with a number
Description: Raise an error when --TESTCD starts with a number

Error Message: The Microscopic Finding test result is not unique for this subject and date/time.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular Microscopic Finding in the MI Domain, for a subject on a particular date.

Error Message: --SPCUFL must be 'N' or null.
Description: Raise an error when record is --SPCUFL is not null and is not equal to 'N'

Error Message: --DTHREF must be 'Y, 'N', 'U' or null.
Description: Raise an error when record is --DTHREL is not null and is not equal to 'Y', 'N' or 'U'

Error Message: The Organ Measurement test is not unique for this subject and date/time.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular Organ Measurement test in the MO Domain, for a subject on a particular date.

Error Message: The palpable mass test and result is not unique for this subject and date/time.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular Palpable Mass test per Palpable Mass test in the PM Domain, for a subject on a particular date.

Error Message: The Pharmacokinetics Concentration test is not unique for this subject or pool and specimen and date/time.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular Pharmacokinetics Concentration, in the PC Domain, for a subject or pool on a particular date.

Error Message: PCSTRESN may not be populated as PCORRES is less than PCLLOQ
Description: If the PCORRES result is less than the Lower Limit of Quantification, then PCSTRESN should be null and not populated with the value of zero (0).

Error Message: The Subject Characteristics test is not unique for this subject.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular Subject Characteristics test for a subject.

Error Message: QNAM > 8 chars
Description: Raise an error when QNAM > 8 chars

Error Message: The Tumor Findings test result is not unique for this subject and specimen.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular tumor test result for a subject and specimen.

Error Message: The Vital Signs test is not unique for this subject and measurement datetime.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular Vital Signs test for a subject and measurement date/time.

Error Message: The ECG test is not unique for this subject and measurement datetime.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular ECG test for a subject and measurement date/time.

Error Message: QNAM may not start with a number
Description: Raise an error when QNAM starts with a number

Error Message: ELEMENT and ETCD do not have a one-to-one relationship.
Description: ETCD and ELEMENT have a one-to-one relationship

Error Message: TEDUR cannot be null when TEENRL is null
Description: Raise an error if TEDUR is null when TEENRL is null

Error Message: The combination of ELEMENT, TESTRL, TEENRL, and TEDUR is not unique for each ETCD
Description: The combination of ELEMENT, TESTRL, TEENRL, and TEDUR must be unique for each ETCD.

Error Message: QNAM value cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers or underscores
Description: Raise an error when QNAM contains anything else than a letter, number or underscore

Error Message: TA.ETCD is not present in TE.ETCD
Description: The values of ETCD used in the Trial Arms dataset must match values for the same Element in the Trial Elements dataset.

Error Message: ARMCD is not present in TA.ARMCD
Description: When study does not use multi-stage arm assignments and ARMCD is populated, ARMCD must be present in TA.ARMCD. This rule has been executed to identify all cases when ARMCD is not present in TA.ARMCD and therefore acknowledges that false positives may be recorded when multi-stage arm assignments are in use.

Error Message: ARMCD is not present in TA.ARMCD
Description: When study does not use multi-stage arm assignments and ARMCD is populated, ARMCD must be present in TA.ARMCD. This rule has been executed to identify all cases when ARMCD is not present in TA.ARMCD and therefore acknowledges that false positives may be recorded when multi-stage arm assignments are in use.

Error Message: ARM is not present in TA.ARM
Description: When study does not use multi-stage arm assignments and ARMCD is populated, ARMCD must be present in TA.ARMCD. This rule has been executed to identify all cases when ARMCD is not present in TA.ARMCD and therefore acknowledges that false positives may be recorded when multi-stage arm assignments are in use.

Error Message: --QNAM value must be uppercase
Description: Raise an error when QNAM has lowercase characters

Error Message: TXSEQ is not unique in TX
Description: TXSEQ should be unique for each record within the TX dataset.

Error Message: TXPARMCD value has more than 8 characters
Description: TXPARMCD Short character value for the Trial Set parameter described in TXPARM.  Maximum 8 characters.

Error Message: The combination of SETCD and SET is not a unique pair
Description: Each SETCD/SET is a unique pair.

Error Message: ETCD value is greater than 8
Description: The length of ETCD should be no greater than 8

Error Message: The value of TXVAL for TXPARMCD=TRTDOS is neither a number, a semicolon-delimited string containing numbers without spaces, or "SEE PROTOCOL"
Description: The value of TRTDOS is either a number, a semicolon-delimited string containing numbers without spaces, or "SEE PROTOCOL" for more complex dosing regimens.

Error Message: The value of TXVAL is not in ISO 8601 date/datetime format
Description: Trial Set Parameters that include dates are required to be presented according to the international standard ISO 8601

Error Message: The value of TXVAL is not may only be "C" or "F" for TXPARMCD=ENTEMPU
Description: The units associated with the environmental temperature; only "C" or "F" is acceptable.

Error Message: The value of TSSEQ is not unique within the value for TSPARMCD
Description: The TSSEQ variable is a unique identifier for each record and is required to identify each record as unique in cases where the same TSPARMCD is used within the dataset.

Error Message: SETCD value is greater than 8
Description: The length of SETCD should be no greater than 8

Error Message: There is a record with TSPARMCD=AGE and there is a record with TSPARMCD=AGETXT
Description: Either the AGE or the AGETXT variable should be populated.

Error Message: The value of TSVAL is not "Y" or "N" for TSPARMCD=SRANDOM
Description: When TSPARMCD=SRANDOM, the value of TSVAL must be either "Y" or "N".

Error Message: Duplicate value of the combination of USUBJID or POOLID with QNAM
Description: There may be only be one record in a SUPP-- dataset with the same QNAM value within USUBJID or POOLID.

Error Message: When populated QORIG may only have one of the values COLLECTED, DERIVED, OTHER, and NOT AVAILABLE
Description: QORIG is used to indicate the origin of the data. Possible values are COLLECTED, DERIVED, OTHER, and NOT AVAILABLE.

Error Message: The record does not have a value for QVAL
Description: All records in the SUPP-- datasets must have a value for QVAL.

Error Message: Length of TSPARMCD is greater than 8
Description: Trigger error when length of TSPARMCD is greater than 8

Error Message: No subject is defined in POOLDEF for POOLID
Description: Trigger error when POOLID does not contain a subject in POOLDEF

Error Message: Variable is not allowed in SDTM/SEND
Description: Trigger when variable cannot be found in the SDTM model (v.1.7 for SENDIG-3.1)

Error Message: ARMCD value length is greater than 20
Description: Verify ARMCD value length is <= 20

Error Message: --TPTREF is empty and --ELTM is not empty
Description: Raise an error when --TPTREF is empty, but --ELTM is not empty

Error Message: When --STAT is "NOT DONE", --REASND must be populated.
Description: Trigger error when --STAT="NOT DONE" and --REASND is not populated

Error Message: The multiple specimens are not correctly separated by a semicolon
Description: If multiple specimen types are used for a calculation (e.g., serum and urine for creatinine clearance), then this field should be populated with values from the (SPEC) Controlled Terminology codelist delimited by a semicolon.

Error Message: Neither --DTC nor --DY is populated
Description: When a domain belongs to the Findings General Observation Class, and the domain is one in which data are usually collected at multiple study days, at least --DTC or --DY must be populated.

Error Message: The relationship between --TPT and --TPTNUM is not a one-to-one relationship
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between the values of --TPT and --TPTNUM

Error Message: Neither --STDTC nor --STDY is populated
Description: Either --STDTC or --STDY must be populated.

Error Message: The relationship between --TPT and --TPTNUM is not a one-to-one relationship
Description: There must be a one-to-one relationship between the values of --TPT and --TPTNUM

Error Message: --TPT is populated but --TPTNUM is not populated
Description: Raise an error when --TPT is populated but --TPTNUM is not populated.

Error Message: --STINT and --ENINT are populated but --TPTREF is not populated
Description: Raise an error when --STINT and -ENINT are populated but --TPTREF is not populated.

Error Message: --STINT and --ENINT must both be populated or none of them must be populated
Description: WHEN --STINT ^= null OR --ENINT ^= null THEN --STINT ^= null  AND --ENINT ^= null

Error Message: Variable name must be in uppercase
Description: Raise an error when variable name is not in uppercase

Error Message: --USCHFL must be either Y or null
Description: --USCHFL must be either Y or null

Error Message: RFXSTDTC does not equal the earliest value of EX.EXSTDTC
Description: Raise an error when EX records are present for subject but RFXSTDTC does not equal the earliest value of EX.EXSTDTC

Error Message: The same SETCD is assigned to different SPECIES
Description: DM records with different values for SPECIES may not have the same SETCD value.

Error Message: The value of COSEQ is not unique within USUBJID
Description: Raise an error when COSEQ is not unique within USUBJID or within POOLID

Error Message: The value of COSEQ is not unique within POOLID
Description: Raise an error when EXDOSE is populated when EXDOSTXT is populated

Error Message: The value of DSSTDTC is not a valid ISO 8601 date/time
Description: Raise an error when the value of DSSTDTC is not a valid ISO 8601 date/time. This automatically excludes composite date/time-s

Error Message: --DTC and --DY are not populated, so --NOMDY must be populated
Description: If --DTC and --DY were not collected, --NOMDY must be populated.

Error Message: DOMAIN value must be uppercase
Description: Raise an error when the value of DOMAIN contains non-uppercase characters

Error Message: The cardiovascular test is not unique for this subject and measurement datetime or evaluation interval.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular cardiovascular test for a subject and measurement date/time or evaluation interval.

Error Message: The respiratory test is not unique for this subject and measurement datetime and/or evaluation interval.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular respiratory test for a subject and measurement date/time or evaluation interval.

Error Message: Only one record with TSPARMCD=SNDIGVER is allowed
Description: Raise an error when there is more than record with TSPARMCD=SNDIGVER

Error Message: Only one record with TSPARMCD=SDESIGN is allowed
Description: Raise an error when there is more than record with TSPARMCD=SDESIGN

Error Message: Only one record with TSPARMCD=SNDCTVER is allowed
Description: Raise an error when there is more than record with TSPARMCD=SNDCTVER

Error Message: Only one record with TSPARMCD=STCAT is allowed
Description: Raise an error when there is more than record with TSPARMCD=STCAT

Error Message: Only one record with TSPARMCD=SSTYP is allowed
Description: Raise an error when there is more than record with TSPARMCD=SSTYP

Error Message: Both USUBJID and POOID are empty
Description: Raise an error when both USUBJID and POOLID are empty

Error Message: --SCAT is equal to --CAT
Description: Trigger error when --SCAT is not null and --SCAT is equal to --CAT

Error Message: --SCAT is equal to DOMAIN
Description: Trigger error when --SCAT is not null and --SCAT is equal to DOMAIN

Error Message: --SCAT is equal to --DECOD
Description: Trigger error when --SCAT is not null and --SCAT is equal to --DECOD or --SCAT is equal to --BODSYS

Error Message: --CAT is equal to DOMAIN
Description: Trigger error when --CAT is not null and --CAT is equal to DOMAIN

Error Message: --CAT is equal to --DECOD
Description: Trigger error when --CAT is not null and --CAT is equal to --DECOD or --SCAT is equal to -BODSYS

Error Message: --ENDTC must be greater than or equal to --DTC
Description: Raise and error when --ENDTC before --DTC

Error Message: --DUR, --EVLINT or --ELTM is not in ISO 8601 Duration format
Description: --EVLINT, --ELTM, --DUR must be in ISO 8601 duration format, including the additional format that allows the representation of  "negative" intervals of time.

Error Message: --TPTREF must be populated when --RFTDTC is populated
Description: Trigger error when --RFTDTC is populated and --TPTREF = null

Error Message: Value length of --TEST is greater than 40.
Description: Raise an error when length of --TEST is greater than 40.

Error Message: Variable value is not in ISO 8601 date / datetime format
Description: Variables that include dates (--DTC) are required to be presented according to the international standard ISO 8601 date or date/time format

Error Message: Variable value is not in correct ISO 8601 date or datetime format
Description: Values of variables RFSTDTC,  RFENDTC, BRTHDTC, --STDTC, --ENDTC, --DTC, --RFTDTC must be correct ISO-8601 dates / datetimes

Error Message: The label of VSTESTCD is invalid
Description: Raise an error when the variable label of VSTESTCD is not 'Vital Signs Test Short Name'

Error Message: One of --DY, --STDY or --ENDY must be populated
Description: One of --DY, --STDY or --ENDY must be populated

Error Message: --DY is not a non-zero integer
--DY is not calculated correctly even though the date portion of --DTC is complete, the date portion of DM.RFSTDTC is a complete date, and --DY is not empty.
Description: Raise an error when --DY is not calculated as per the study day algorithm as a non-zero integer value when the date portion of --DTC is complete and the date portion of DM.RFSTDTC is a complete date AND --DY is not empty

Error Message: --DY is not calculated correctly even though the date portion of --DTC is complete, the date portion of DM.RFSTDTC is a complete date, and --DY is not empty.
Description: Raise an error when --DY is not calculated as per the study day algorithm as a non-zero integer value when the date portion of --DTC is complete and the date portion of DM.RFSTDTC is a complete date AND --DY is not empty

Error Message: --ORRES must be populated as --STAT is not equal to 'NOT DONE'
Description: There should always be data presented in the --ORRES variable unless  --STAT = "NOT DONE".

Error Message: --STRESC must be be populated as --ORRES is populated.
Description: When --ORRES is populated, --STRESC must also be populated.

Error Message: --STRESC must be populated as --ORRES is populated
Description: When --STRESC represents numeric data, --STRESN must be populated.

Error Message: --STRESN may not be populated as --ORRES does not represent a pure numeric value
Description: When --ORRES is representing numeric data with special characters like '<' and '>', , --STRESN may not be populated.

Error Message: USUBJID is not unique within DM
Description: DM - One record per subject

Error Message: The filename is not equal to the 2-character domain code.
Description: Raise an error when the filename is not equal to the value of DOMAIN.

Error Message: The Body Weight test is not unique for this subject and date/time.
Description: Raise an error when there is more than one record present for any particular Body Weight test, in the BW Domain, for a subject on a particular date.

Error Message: The mass identification is not unique within the subject regardless of the mass location.
Description: Raise an error when the mass identification is not unique within the subject, regardless of the mass location.

Error Message: IECAT equals "INCLUSION" and IEORRES is not equal to "N".
Description: Raise an error when IECAT="INCLUSION" and IEORRES^="N".

Error Message: SESTDTC is required.
Description: Raise an error when SESTDTC is null.

Error Message: TRLOC is present when TRLOC is not included in the TR domain.
Description: Raise an error when TRLOC is present.

Error Message: ECOCCUR indicates dose was not given, but ECDOSE is not blank or has a value less than or equal to 0
Description: When ECOCCUR indicates no dose, then ECDOSE needs to be null or > 0; it cannot be used to indicate a dose wasn't taken.

Error Message: EXTRT is PLACEBO, but EXDOSE is not equal to 0.
Description: When EXTRT is PLACEBO, EXDOSE must equal 0

Error Message: DTHFL is not "Y" or null
Description: Raise an error when DTHFL ^= "Y" and not null

Error Message: DTHFL is not "Y", when DTHDTC is populated
Description: Raise an error when DTHDTC is not empty and DTHFL not equal to "Y"

Error Message: DTHFL is not "Y", when SS.SSSTRESC equals "DEAD"
Description: Raise an error when DTHFL not equal to "Y" and SS.SSSTRESC = "DEAD".

Error Message: ELEMENT variable has a non-null value when ETCD has a value of 'UNPLAN'
Description: Verify that ELEMENT value is blank when ETCD is equal to UNPLAN

Error Message: ARMCD value length is greater than 20

Error Message: RELTYPE is populated when IDVAR is populated with a --SEQ value.
Description: When IDVAR is populated with a --SEQ value, RELTYPE must be null.

Error Message: The combination of IDVAR, IDVARVAL, and QNAM is not unique per parent subject record
Description: Trigger error when the combination of IDVAR, IDVARVAL, and QNAM is not unique per parent subject record

Error Message: Scheduled or Contingent visit is not unique within subject
Description: When VISITNUM is present in TV.VISITNUM, SV.VISITNUM must be unique within subject

Error Message: --ULOQ is not expressed using the units in --STRESU
Description: Trigger error when --ULOQ is not expressed using the units in --STRESU

Error Message: IDVARVAL does not equal a value of variable=IDVAR in domain=RDOMAIN
Description: When IDVAR is populated, IDVARVAL must equal a value of the variable referenced by IDVAR within the domain referenced by RDOMAIN

Error Message: --STDTC is present in a Findings general observation class
Description: Trigger error when --STDTC is present in a Findings general observation class

Error Message: ACTARMCD is not in in TA.ARMCD
Description: Trigger error when study does not use multi-stage arm assignments and ACTARMCD ^= null, and ACTARMCD is not in TA.ARMCD

Error Message: ACTARM value in DM dataset is not among the values of ARM variable in the TA dataset. This is allowed only in a multistage study with incomplete ARM assignment. Please confirm if your study is a multistage assignment study.
Description: When study does not use multi-stage arm assignments and ACTARM is populated, ACTARM must be present in TA.ARM. This rule has been executed to identify all cases when ACTARM is not present in TA.ARM and therefore acknowledges that false positives may be recorded when multi-stage arm assignments are in use.

Error Message: ARMCD is not present in TA.ARMCD
Description: When study does not use multi-stage arm assignments and ARMCD is populated, ARMCD must be present in TA.ARMCD. This rule has been executed to identify all cases when ARMCD is not present in TA.ARMCD and therefore acknowledges that false positives may be recorded when multi-stage arm assignments are in use.

Error Message: Population flag is present in SUPPDM
Description: SUPPDM must not include population flags.

Error Message: DSSCAT is not present when subject has more than one record per Epoch with DSCAT = 'DISPOSITION EVENT'.
Description: When subject has more than one record per Epoch with DSCAT = DISPOSITION EVENT, DSSCAT must be present.

Error Message: More than one record per subject per DSSCAT per EPOCH
Description: Trigger error when there is more than one record per subject per DSSCAT per EPOCH

Error Message: There is more than 1 record per subject has DSSCAT = 'STUDY PARTICIPATION'
Description: Trigger error when more than 1 record per subject has DSSCAT = 'STUDY PARTICIPATION'

Error Message: There is more than 1 record per subject has DSSCAT = 'STUDY TREATMENT'
Description: Trigger error when there is more than 1 record per subject has DSSCAT = 'STUDY TREATMENT'

Error Message: MIDSTYPE is not unique within subject when MIDSTYPE = TM.MIDSTYPE and TM.TMRPT = 'N'
Description: MIDSTYPE must be unique within subject when MIDSTYPE = TM.MIDSTYPE and TM.TMRPT = 'N'

Error Message: ECDOSE is empty, ECOCCUR is not equal to 'N' and ECSTAT is empty, but ECDOSTXT is also empty.
Description: Raise an error when ECDOSE is empty, ECOCCUR is not equal to 'N', ECSTAT is empty and ECDOSTXT is empty

Error Message: IDVAR is empty but IDVARVAL is not empty
Description: Raise an error when IDVAR is empty and IDVARVAL is not empty

Error Message: --SCAT is equal to domain dataset label.
Description: Raise an error when --SCAT = domain dataset label.

Error Message: --TESTCD > 8 chars or contains more than only letters, numbers, underscores, or starts with a number.
Description: Raise an error when --TESTCD > 8 chars or contains more than only letters, numbers and underscores, or starts with a number.

Error Message: QNAM > 8 chars or contains letters that are in not in uppercase, more than only letters, numbers, underscores, or starts with a number.
Description: Raise an error when QNAM > 8 chars or contains more than only letters in uppercase, numbers and underscores, or starts with a number.

Error Message: QLABEL > 40 chars.
Description: Raise an error when QLABEL > 40 chars.

Error Message: ACTARMCD is empty, but ARMNRS is not completed.
Description: Raise an error when ACTARMCD is empty and ARMNRS is not completed.

Error Message: ACTARM is empty, but ARMNRS is not completed.
Description: Raise an error when ACTARM is empty and ARMNRS is not completed.

Error Message: --STAT should be "NOT DONE" when --REASND is provided.
Description: Raise an error when --REASND is provided and --STAT is not equal to "NOT DONE".

Error Message: --DTHREL must never be used in SDTM-based data for human clinical trials
Description: Verifying presence of SEND variable --DTHREL

Error Message: IETEST is not in TI.IETEST
Description: Check if IETEST is not in TI.IETEST

Error Message: IETESTCD from IE domain does not exist in IETESTCD of TI domain.
Description: Check if IETESTCD is present in TI.IETESTCD

Error Message: POOLID must be null when USUBJID is populated
Description: Verify that When USUBJID is populated, POOLID is not populated

Error Message: USUBJID must be null when POOLID is populated
Description: Verify that when POOLID is populated, USUBJID is not populated

Error Message: RSUBJID when populated cannot equal USUBJID
Description: Verify that when RSUBJID populated , RSUBJID does not equal USUBJID

Error Message: When RSUBJID is populated, RUSBJID cannot equal POOLID
Description: Verify when RSUBJID is populated it does not equal POOLID

Error Message: RDEVID must be empty when RSUBJID is populated and RSUBJID must be empty when RDEVID is populated
Description: Related Device Identifier (RDEVID) and Related Subject or Pool Identifier (RSUBJID) should not both be populated for the same record.

Error Message: RSUBJID must be missing when RDEVID is populated
Description: Verify that RSUBJID is empty when RDEVID is populated

Error Message: RSUBJID must equal DM.USUBJID when RSUBJID is populated and RSUBJID does not equal POOLID
Description: Verify that RSUBJID=DM.USUBJID when RSUBJID is populated and RSUBJID is not equal to POOLID

Error Message: MHSTDTC ^= null and MHSTDTC is on or after the DM.RFSTDTC. The medical history dataset should include the subject's prior history at the start of the trial.
Description: Raise an issue if MHSTDTC has a non-empty date that later than DM.RFSTDTC

Error Message: --SCAT is equal to --CAT
Description: Trigger error when --SCAT is not null and --SCAT is equal to --CAT

Error Message: RFXENDTC does not equal the latest value of EX.EXSTDTC or EX.EXENDTC
Description: Raise an error when EX records are present for subject but RFXENDTC does not equal the latest value of EX.EXSTDTC or EX.EXENDTC

Error Message: RFXSTDTC does not equal the earliest value of EX.EXSTDTC
Description: Raise an error when EX records are present for subject but RFXSTDTC does not equal the earliest value of EX.EXSTDTC

Error Message: --STRF is populated when --OCCUR = "N"
Description: When --OCCUR = 'N', --STRF must not be populated

Error Message: --ENRF is populated when --OCCUR = "N"
Description: When --OCCUR = 'N', --ENRF must not be populated

Error Message: --EXCLFL must never be used in SDTM-based human trials
Description: Raise an error when --EXCLFL is present in dataset.

Error Message: --REASEX must never be used in SDTM-based human clinical trials
Description: Raise an error when --REASEX is present in dataset.

Error Message: --DETECT must never be used in SDTM-based human trials
Description: Raise an error when --DETECT is present in dataset.

Error Message: --NOMDY is present.
Description: Raise an error when --NOMDY is present.

Error Message: --NOMLBL is present.
Description: Raise an error when --NOMLBL is present.

Error Message: --RESLOC is present.
Description: Raise an error when --RESLOC is present.

Error Message: --RFTDTC is populated when --TPTREF is null
Description: Trigger error when --TPTREF = null and --RFTDTC is populated

Error Message: Visit Day cannot be found in Trial Visit (TV) domain
Description: Verify that visitdy is planned and exists in TV

Error Message: MHENDTC ^= null and MHENDTC is on or after the DM.RFSTDTC. The medical history dataset should include the subject's prior history at the start of the trial.
Description: Raise an issue if MHENDTC has a non-empty date that is on or after DM.RFSTDTC

Error Message: DSDECOD is not "DEATH", When SS.SSSTRESC = "DEAD".
Description: When SS.SSSTRESC = "DEAD", the final disposition record must have DSDECOD ^= "DEATH".

Error Message: DTHFL is not 'Y' when DS.DECOD is "DEATH"
Description: When DS.DSDECOD is 'DEATH', DTHFL must be 'Y'

Error Message: DTHFL is not 'Y' when AE.AESDTH is 'Y'.
Description: When AE.AESDTH is 'Y', DTHFL must be 'Y'

Error Message: DTHFL is not 'Y' when AE.AEOUT is 'FATAL'.
Description: When AE.AEOUT is 'FATAL', DTHFL must be 'Y'

Error Message: --ORRES must be populated as --STAT is not equal to 'NOT DONE'
Description: There should always be data presented in the --ORRES variable unless  --STAT = "NOT DONE".

Error Message: Missing value for SEUPDES, when ETCD='UNPLAN'
Description: Raise an error when ETCD = 'UNPLAN', SEUPDES = null

Error Message: --STRTPT is completed, but --STTPT is not completed.
Description: Raise an error when --STRTPT is completed and --STTPT is not completed.

Error Message: --STRTPT is present in dataset, but --STTPT is not present in dataset.
Description: Raise an error when --STRTPT is present in dataset and --STTPT is not present in dataset.

Error Message: SSSTRESC = 'DEAD', but SSDTC < DM.DTHDTC.
Description: Raise an error when SSSTRESC = 'DEAD' and SSDTC < DM.DTHDTC.

Error Message: --PRESP does not equal 'Y' or is not empty.
Description: Raise an error when --PRESP does not equal 'Y' or is not empty.

Error Message: --STTPT is present in dataset, but --STRTPT is not present in dataset.
Description: Raise an error when --STTPT is present in dataset and --STRTPT is not present in dataset.

Error Message: RFSTDTC in DM dataset is empty but --STRF is completed.
Description: Raise an error when RFSTDTC in DM is empty and --STRF is not empty.

Error Message: Variable name length is greater than 8.
Description: Raise an error when variable name length is greater than 8.

Error Message: Primary analysis used but --BODSYS and --SOC are not equal
Description: Raise an error if primary SOC is used for analysis and -BODSYS is not equal to -SOC

Error Message: --ENRTPT is completed, but --ENTPT is not completed.
Description: Raise an error when --ENRTPT is completed and --ENTPT is not completed.

Error Message: If AESER = "N" then none of the seriousness criteria (AESCAN, AESCONG, AESDISAB, AESDTH, AESHOSP, AESLIFE, AESOD, AESMIE) could be equal to "Y".
Description: Select record where AESCAN and AESCONG and AESDISAB and AESDTH and AESHOSP and AESLIFE and AESOD and AESMIE ^= "Y" However, AESER ^= "N"

Error Message: --DECOD should be populated when --PTCD is populated
Description: Raise an error when --DECOD is not populated but --PTCD is populated

Error Message: --DECOD and --PTCD do not have a one-to-one relationship
Description: Trigger error when --DECOD and --PTCD do not have a one-to-one relationship

Error Message: For a planned visit (SVPRESP = 'Y'), non-missing VISIT value must be among those present in TV.VISIT.
Description: Verify when VISIT is not null in any given domain and VISIT is planned (SVPRESP = 'Y'), then VISIT should be among TV.VISIT.

Error Message: For a planned visit (SVPRESP = 'Y'), non-missing VISITNUM value must be among those present in TV.VISITNUM. in TV.VISITNUM
Description: Verify when VISITNUM is not null in any given domain and VISITNUM is planned (SVPRESP = 'Y'), then VISIT should be among TV.VISITNUM.

Error Message: Variable value not found in non-extensible codelist.
Description: Variable must be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist. New terms cannot be added into non-extensible codelists.

Error Message: Variable value not found in non-extensible codelist
Description: Variable must be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist. New terms cannot be added into non-extensible codelists.

Error Message: Variable value not found in extensible codelist
Description: Variable should be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist. New terms can be added as long as they are not duplicates, synonyms or subsets of existing standard terms.

Error Message: Coded and Decoded values do not have the same Code in CDISC CT
Description: Paired variables such as TEST/TESTCD must be populated using terms with the same Codelist Code value in CDISC control terminology. There is one-to-one relationship between paired variable values defined in CDISC control terminology by Codelist Code value.

Error Message: Variable value not found in non-extensible codelist when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable must be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist, when its value level condition is met. New terms cannot be added into non-extensible codelists.

Error Message: Variable value not found in extensible codelist when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable should be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist, when its value level condition is met. New terms can be added as long as they are not duplicates, synonyms or subsets of existing standard terms.

Error Message: Coded and Decoded values do not have the same Code in CDISC CT when value-level condition occurs
Description: Paired variables such as TEST/TESTCD must be populated using terms with the same Codelist Code value in CDISC control terminology. There is one-to-one relationship between paired variable values defined in CDISC control terminology by Codelist Code value within the same value level condition.

Error Message: No records in data source
Description: Domain table should have at least one record.

Error Message: NULL value in variable marked as Required
Description: Required variables (where Core attribute is 'Req') cannot be NULL for any records.

Error Message: Invalid ISO 8601 value for variable
Description: Value of Dates/Time variables (*DTC) must conform to the ISO 8601 international standard.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for DOMAIN
Description: Domain Abbreviation (DOMAIN) variable should be consistent with the name of the dataset.

Error Message: Duplicate value for --SEQ variable
Description: The value of Sequence Number (--SEQ) variable must be unique for each record within a domain and within each Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) or Pool Identifier (POOLID) variables value when they are present in the domain. Exclusions are DO, DT, DU and DX domains.

Error Message: No baseline flag record in Domain for subject
Description: All subjects should have at least one baseline observation (--BLFL = 'Y') in EG, LB, MB, MS, PC and VS domains, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL') or were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN') or were not treated (ACTARMCD = 'NOTTRT').

Error Message: Inconsistent value for Standard Units
Description: Standard Units (--STRESU) must be consistent for all records with the same Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TESTCD), Object of the Observation (--OBJ), Measurement,Test, or Examination Detail (--TSTDTL), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Specimen Type (--SPEC) and Method of Test or Examination (--METHOD).

Error Message: Value for --DECOD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for the Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD) variable must be populated using a Preferred Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Error Message: Value for --DECOD is in incorrect case
Description: Case for the Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD) variable must be sentence case using a Preferred Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-sensitive).

Error Message: No qualifiers set to 'Y', when AE is Serious
Description: When Serious Event (AESER) variable value is 'Y', then at least one of seriousness criteria variables is expected to have value 'Y' (Involves Cancer (AESCAN), Congenital Anomaly or Birth Defect (AESCONG), Persist or Signif Disability/Incapacity (AESDISAB), Results in Death (AESDTH), Requires or Prolongs Hospitalization (AESHOSP), Is Life Threatening (AESLIFE), or Other Medically Important Serious Event (AESMIE)).

Error Message: ARM is not 'Screen Failure', when ARMCD equals 'SCRNFAIL', or vice versa
Description: Description of Arm (ARM) must equal 'Screen Failure',  when Arm Code (ARMCD) is 'SCRNFAIL', and vice versa.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --DRVFL='Y'
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Format (--STRESC) value should not be NULL, when Derived Flag (--DRVFL) value is 'Y'.

Error Message: Invalid value for --TEST variable
Description: The value of Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST) should be no more than 40 characters in length.

Error Message: Invalid value for --TESTCD variable
Description: The value of a Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TESTCD) variable should be limited to 8 characters, cannot start with a number, and cannot contain characters other than letters in upper case, numbers, or underscores.

Error Message: Invalid value for --PARM variable
Description: The value of Parameter (--PARM) variable should be no more than 40 characters in length.

Error Message: Invalid value for --PARMCD variable
Description: The value of Parameter Short Name (--PARMCD) variables should be no more than 8 characters in length.

Error Message: Missing End Time-Point value
Description: One End Time-Point variable is expected to be populated when an event or an intervention occurred. (E.g., End Date/Time of Event or Intervention (--ENDTC), or End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF), or End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRTPT) should not be missing, or Occurrence (--OCCUR) = 'N' or Completion Status (--STAT) != '') or Duration (--DUR) != '').

Error Message: Missing Start Time-Point value
Description: One Start Time-Point variable is expected to be populated when an event or intervention occurred. (E.g., Start Date/Time of Event or Intervention (--STDTC), or Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF), or Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRTPT) should not be missing, or Occurrence (--OCCUR) = 'N' or Completion Status (--STAT) != '').

Error Message: Missing value for --STAT, when --REASND is provided
Description: Completion Status (--STAT) should be set to 'NOT DONE', when Reason Not Done (--REASND) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --ORRESU, when --ORRES is provided
Description: Original Units (--ORRESU) should not be NULL, when Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) is provided is a numeric result.

Error Message: Missing value for --ORRES, when --ORRESU is provided
Description: Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) should not be NULL, when Original Units (--ORRESU) is provided.

Error Message: Value for --STNRHI is less than value for --STNRLO
Description: Reference Range Upper Limit-Std Units (--STNRHI) value must be greater than or equal to Reference Range Lower Limit-Std Units (--STNRLO) value.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRESU, when --STRESC is provided
Description: Standard Units (--STRESU) should not be NULL, when Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) is provided as a numeric result.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --STRESU is provided
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) should not be NULL, when Standard Units (--STRESU) is provided.

Error Message: Missing values for --STDTC, --STRF and --STRTPT, when --ENDTC, --ENRF or --ENRTPT is provided
Description: Start Date/Time of Observation (--STDTC), Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF) or Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) should not be NULL, when End Date/Time of Observation (--ENDTC), End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF) or End Relative to Reference Time Period (--ENRTPT) is not NULL.

Error Message: Missing value for --TPT, when --TPTNUM is provided
Description: Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) should not be NULL, when Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --TPTNUM, when --TPT is provided
Description: Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) should not be NULL, when Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --TPTREF, when --ELTM is provided
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) should not be NULL, when Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref (--ELTM) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --DOSU, when --DOSE, --DOSTXT or --DOSTOT is provided
Description: Dose Units (--DOSU) must be populated, when Dose per Administration (--DOSE), Dose Description (--DOSTXT) or Total Daily Dose (--DOSTOT) is provided.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --ORRES is provided
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) must be populated, when Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) is provided.

Error Message: Value for variable not found in user-defined codelist
Description: Variable values should be populated with terms found in the user-defined codelist associated with the variable in define.xml.

Error Message: Value of Study Day variable equals 0
Description: Study Day variables (*DY) value should not equal 0.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --TEST within --TESTCD
Description: All values of Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST) should be the same for a given value of Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TESTCD).

Error Message: Value for --OCCUR is populated for unsolicited Intervention or Event
Description: Occurrence (--OCCUR) may only be populated, when a given Intervention or Event has been pre-specified (--PRESP = 'Y').

Error Message: --STAT does not equal 'NOT DONE', when --PRESP='Y' and --OCCUR is NULL
Description: When no response is provided for Occurrence (--OCCUR) for a pre-specified Intervention or Event (--PRESP = 'Y'), then Status (--STAT) should be set to 'NOT DONE'.

Error Message: Missing value for --TRTV, when --VAMT is not NULL
Description: Treatment Vehicle (--TRTV) should be provided, when Treatment Vehicle Amount (--VAMT) is specified.

Error Message: Missing value for --VAMTU, when --VAMT is populated
Description: Treatment Vehicle Amount Units (--VAMTU) should not be NULL,  when Treatment Vehicle Amount (--VAMT) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --RESCAT is populated
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) should be provided, when Result Category (--RESCAT) is specified.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for QLABEL within QNAM
Description: All values of Qualifier Variable Label (QLABEL) should be the same for a given value of Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM).

Error Message: Missing value for --ORRES, when --STAT or --DRVFL is not populated
Description: Status (--STAT) should be set to 'NOT DONE' or Derived Flag (--DRVFL) should have a value of 'Y', when Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) is NULL.

Error Message: Missing value for --STTPT, when --STRTPT is populated
Description: Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) must not be NULL, when Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) is provided.

Error Message: Missing value for --ENTPT, when --ENRTPT is populated
Description: End Reference Time Point (--ENTPT) must not be NULL, when End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) is provided.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for VISIT within VISITNUM
Description: All values of Visit Name (VISIT) should be the same for a given value of Visit Number (VISITNUM).

Error Message: Inconsistent value for VISITNUM within VISIT
Description: All values of Visit Number (VISITNUM) should be the same for a given value of Visit Name (VISIT).

Error Message: ARM is not 'Not Assigned', when ARMCD equals 'NOTASSGN', or vice versa
Description: Description of Arm (ARM) must equal 'Not Assigned', when Arm Code (ARMCD) is 'NOTASSGN', and vice versa.

Error Message: Variable in define.xml is not present in the dataset
Description: Variables listed in the data definition document (define.xml) should be included in the dataset.

Error Message: SDTM/dataset variable type mismatch
Description: Variable Data Types in the dataset should match the variable data types described in SDTM.

Error Message: SDTM Required variable not found
Description: Variables described in SDTM IG as Required must be included in the dataset.

Error Message: SDTM Expected variable not found
Description: Variables described in SDTM IG as Expected should be included in the dataset.

Error Message: Variable appears in dataset, but is not in SDTM model
Description: Only variables listed in SDTM model should appear in a dataset. New sponsor defined variables must not be added, and existing variables must not be renamed or modified.

Error Message: Define.xml/dataset variable type mismatch
Description: Variable DataType in define.xml must match variable Type in dataset. Define-XML data types of 'integer' and 'float' match dataset type of 'Num', all other match 'Char'.

Error Message: Variable in dataset is not present in define.xml
Description: Variables included in the dataset must be described in the data definition document (define.xml).

Error Message: Domain referenced in define.xml but dataset is missing
Description: Domains referenced in data definition document (define.xml) should be included in the submission.

Error Message: Incompatible data source
Description: Domain table must have a valid format (e.g., SAS transport (XPORT) v.5 or text-delimited).

Error Message: SDTM/dataset variable label mismatch
Description: Variable Label in the dataset should match the variable label described in SDTM IG. When creating a new domain Variable Labels could be adjusted as appropriate to properly convey the meaning in the context of the data being submitted.

Error Message: SDTM/dataset variable label mismatch
Description: Variable Label in the dataset should match the variable label described in SDTM IG. When creating a new domain Variable Labels could be adjusted as appropriate to properly convey the meaning in the context of the data being submitted.

Error Message: Subject is not present in DM domain
Description: All Subjects (USUBJID) must be present in Demographics (DM) domain.

Error Message: USUBJID/VISIT/VISITNUM values do not match SV domain data
Description: All Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) + Visit Name (VISIT) + Visit Number (VISITNUM) combination values in data should be present in the Subject Visits (SV) domain. There is an exception for records, where Status (--STAT) variable value is populated. E.g., --STAT = 'NOT DONE'. Another exception is for records, where Occurrence (ECOCCUR) is 'N' in EC domain.

Error Message: Invalid ARMCD
Description: Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL') or were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN').

Error Message: Invalid ETCD
Description: Element Code (ETCD) values should match entries in the Trial Elements (TE) dataset, except for unplanned Element (ETCD = 'UNPLAN').

Error Message: Invalid IETESTCD
Description: A value for Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Short Name (IETESTCD) must be present the Trial Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria (TI) domain.

Error Message: No Disposition record found for subject
Description: All Demographics (DM) subjects (USUBJID) should have at least one record in the Disposition (DS) domain. The only possible exceptions for SDTMIG v3.2 (and earlier) are Screen Failures (ARMCD=SCRNFAIL) and Not Assigned Treatment (ARMCD=NOTASSGN) subjects, or subjects with ARMCD=null.  There are no exceptions for SEND.

Error Message: No Exposure record found for subject
Description: All Demographics (DM) subjects (USUBJID) participating in a study that includes investigational product should have at least one record in the Exposure (EX) domain, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL'), were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN'), or did not receive study treatment (ACTARMCD = 'NOTTRT').

Error Message: Invalid ARM/ARMCD
Description: The combination of Description of Planned Arm (ARM) and Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) values must match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL') or were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN').

Error Message: Invalid RDOMAIN
Description: Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN) must have a valid value of Domains included in the study data.

Error Message: Invalid IDVAR
Description: Identifying Variable (IDVAR) must have a valid value of variables from a referenced Domain.

Error Message: Invalid referenced record
Description: Reference record defined by Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN), Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID), Identifying Variable (IDVAR) and Identifying Variable Value (IDVARVAL) must exist in the target Domain.

Error Message: EX record is present, when subject is not assigned to an arm
Description: Subjects that are not assigned to an Arm (ARMCD='NOTASSGN') or are screen failures (ARMCD='SCRNFAIL'), or ARM=null, should not have any Exposure records. Run-in records (EPOCH='RUN-IN') are excluded from firing for this validation rule.

Error Message: AE start date is after the latest Disposition date
Description: Start Date/Time of Adverse Event (AESTDTC) should be less than or equal to the Start Date/Time of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDTC).

Error Message: Exposure end date is after the latest Disposition date
Description: End Date/Time of Treatment (EXENDTC) should be less than or equal to the Start Date/Time of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDTC).

Error Message: Duplicate USUBJID in DM within STUDYID
Description: The value of Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variable must be unique for each subject across all trials in the submission. In the Demographics (DM) domain, there should only be one record per subject.

Error Message: Negative or zero value for AGE
Description: The value of Age (AGE) cannot be less than or equal to 0.

Error Message: Mismatch between IEORRES and IESTRESC values
Description: I/E Criterion Original Result (IEORRES) and I/E Criterion Result in Std Format (IESTRESC) should have the same value.

Error Message: SUPPQUAL duplicate records
Description: All SUPPQUAL Domains records are associated with a single parent record and must have a unique combination of Study Identifier (STUDYID), Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID), Identifying Variable (IDVAR), Identifying Variable Value (IDVARVAL) and Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM) variable value. For all SUPPQUAL domain record all The QNAM variable should be unique for each parent record.

Error Message: RFSTDTC is not provided for a randomized subject
Description: Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) should be populated for all randomized subjects, those where Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) is not equal to 'SCRNFAIL' or 'NOTASSGN' or null.

Error Message: RFENDTC is not provided for a randomized subject
Description: Subject Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC) should be populated for all randomized subjects, those where Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) is not equal to 'SCRNFAIL' or 'NOTASSGN' or null.

Error Message: Missing values for TEENRL and TEDUR
Description: At least one of Rule for End of Element (TEENRL) or Planned Duration of Element (TEDUR) should be populated.

Error Message: AESDTH is not 'Y', when AEOUT='FATAL'
Description: Results in Death (AESDTH) should equal 'Y', when Outcome of Adverse Event (AEOUT)  is 'FATAL'.

Error Message: AEOUT is not 'FATAL', when AESDTH='Y'
Description: Outcome of Adverse Event should equal 'FATAL', when Results in Death (AESDTH) is 'Y'.

Error Message: Missing value for SEUPDES, when ETCD='UNPLAN'
Description: Description of Unplanned Element (SEUPDES) should be populated, when subject's experience for a particular period of time is represented as an unplanned Element, where Element Code (ETCD) is equal to 'UNPLAN'.

Error Message: Missing value for AGEU, when AGE is provided
Description: Age Units (AGEU) should be provided, when Age (AGE) is populated.

Error Message: Invalid usage of SUPPQUAL for non-general-observation-class Domain
Description: Supplemental Qualifiers special purpose dataset (SUPP--) can only be used to capture non-standard variables and their association to parent records in general-observation-class datasets (Events, Findings, Interventions) and Demographics. Another exception is Subject Visits domain in SDTM-IG prior v3.4

Error Message: Duplicate SUBJID
Description: The value of Subject Identifier for the Study (SUBJID) variable must be unique for each subject within the study.

Error Message: RFSTDTC is after RFENDTC
Description: Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) must be less than or equal to Subject Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC).

Error Message: Missing value for AGE, when AGEU is provided
Description: Age (AGE) should be provided, when Age Units (AGEU) are populated.

Error Message: Invalid value for ARMCD
Description: The value of Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) should be no more than 20 characters in length.

Error Message: Invalid STUDYID
Description: Study Identifier (STUDYID) values must match the STUDYID in Demographics (DM) domain.

Error Message: CODTC is populated, when comment is a child record of another domain
Description: The value of Date/Time of Comment (CODTC) should be NULL, when comments are related to a specific parent record or group of parent records in a domain (RDOMAIN, IDVAR and IDVARVAL are populated).

Error Message: Invalid value for ETCD
Description: The value of Element Code (ETCD) should be no more than 8 characters in length.

Error Message: ELEMENT value is populated, when ETCD= 'UNPLAN'
Description: Description of Element (ELEMENT) should be NULL, when subject's experience for a particular period of time is represented as an unplanned Element, where Element Code (ETCD) is equal to 'UNPLAN'.

Error Message: Invalid ISO 8601 value for variable
Description: Value of Duration, Elapsed Time, and Interval variables (--DUR, --ELTM, --EVLINT, --STINT, --ENINT, TDSTOFF, TDTGTPAI, TDMINPAI, TDMAXPAI) must conform to the ISO 8601 international standard.

Error Message: Invalid ETCD/ELEMENT
Description: The combination of Element Code (ETCD) and Description of Element (ELEMENT) values should match entries in the Trial Elements (TE) dataset, except for unplanned Element (ETCD = 'UNPLAN').

Error Message: TAETORD is populated, ETCD = 'UNPLAN'
Description: Planned Order of Elements within Arm (TAETORD) should be NULL, when subject's experience for a particular period of time is represented as an unplanned Element (ETCD = 'UNPLAN').

Error Message: Invalid TAETORD
Description: Order of Element within Arm (TAETORD) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset.

Error Message: Invalid EPOCH
Description: Epoch (EPOCH) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset.

Error Message: Invalid IETESTCD/IETEST/IECAT
Description: The combination of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Short Name (IETESTCD), Criterion (IETEST), and Category (IECAT) values should match entries in the Trial Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria (TI) dataset.

Error Message: VISITNUM value does not match TV domain data
Description: Visit Number (VISITNUM) values should match entries in the Trial Visits (TV) dataset, when they are planned visits (SVUPDES = NULL).

Error Message: VISITNUM/VISIT/VISITDY values do not match TV domain data
Description: The combination of Visit Number (VISITNUM), Visit Name (VISIT), and Planned Study Day of Visit (VISITDY) values should match entries in the Trial Visits (TV) dataset, when they are planned visits (SVUPDES = NULL).

Error Message: VISITDY is populated for unplanned visit
Description: Planned Study Day of Visit (VISITDY) should equal NULL for unplanned visits, where Description of Unplanned Visit (SVUPDES) is populated.

Error Message: Missing DM dataset
Description: Demographics (DM) dataset must be included in every submission.

Error Message: Unexpected character value in variable
Description: Character values should not have leading space ' ' characters, carriage returns, or '.' as an entire value. The only exceptions are COVALn and TSVALn variables.

Error Message: Invalid value for QNAM variable
Description: The value of Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM) should be limited to 8 characters, cannot start with a number, and cannot contain characters other than letters in upper case, numbers, or underscores.

Error Message: VISIT/VISITNUM values do not match TV domain data
Description: Combination of Visit Name (VISIT) and Visit Number (VISITNUM) in subject-level domains should match that in the TV domain with the exception of Unscheduled and Unplanned visits.

Error Message: Invalid value for RELTYPE variable
Description: Relationship Type (RELTYPE) must be NULL, when Identifying Variable (IDVAR) is populated with a --SEQ value.

Error Message: Non-unique value for ELEMENT within ETCD
Description: Description of Element (ELEMENT) must have a unique value for a given value of Element Code (ETCD) within the domain.

Error Message: Non-ASCII or non-printable characters in variable
Description: Variables value must not include non-ASCII or non-printable characters (outside of 32-126 ASCII code range), limited to variables which values may be converted into new variable name or label (--TEST, --TESTCD, --PARM, --PARMCD, QLABEL, QNAM).

Error Message: Value for --STRF is populated, when RFSTDTC is NULL
Description: Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF) should not be populated for subjects with missing value for Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC).

Error Message: Value for --ENRF is populated, when RFENDTC is NULL
Description: End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF) should not be populated for subjects with missing value for Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC).

Error Message: No records for 'SCRNFAIL' subject are found in IE domain
Description: All subjects with Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) equals 'SCRNFAIL' should have records in the Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria Not Met (IE) domain.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for ARM
Description: A value for Description of Planned Arm (ARM) must have a unique value for Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) with the domain.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for ARMCD
Description: A value for Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) must have a unique value for Description of Planned Arm (ARM) with the domain.

Error Message: Missing value for DSCAT
Description: Category for Disposition Event (DSCAT) should be populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --TOXGR, when --TOX is populated
Description: Toxicity Grade (--TOXGR) should be provided, when Toxicity (--TOX) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --TOX, when --TOXGR is populated
Description: A value for a Toxicity (--TOX) variable should be provided, when a Toxicity Grade (--TOXGR) variable value is populated and greater than 0.

Error Message: Non-unique value for TSSEQ variable within TSPARMCD
Description: Sequence Number (TSSEQ) must have a  unique value for a given value of Trial Summary Parameter Short Name (TSPARMCD) within the domain.

Error Message: --CAT value is redundant with other variable values
Description: Value of Category (--CAT) should not be identical to that in Domain Abbreviation (DOMAIN); Reported Term (--TERM); Name of Measurement, Test, or Examination (--TESTCD); Name of Treatment (--TRT); Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS).

Error Message: --SCAT value is redundant with other variable values
Description: Value of Subcategory (--SCAT) should not be  identical to that in Domain Abbreviation (DOMAIN); Reported Term (--TERM); Name of Measurement, Test, or Examination (--TESTCD); Name of Treatment (--TRT); Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS).

Error Message: Values for --CAT and --SCAT are identical
Description: Values of Category (--CAT) and Subcategory (--SCAT) variables should not be identical.

Error Message: Time point for non-occurred event or intervention is provided
Description: Value of Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF) or End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF) should not be populated, when an event or intervention is marked as not occurred (--OCCUR='N').

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --TESTCD within --TEST
Description: All values of Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TESTCD) should be the same for a given value of Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST).

Error Message: No --BLFL variable in custom Findings domain
Description: Baseline Flag (--BLFL) should be present in all custom Findings domains.

Error Message: Inconsistent values for IEORRES/IECAT
Description: I/E Criterion Original Result (IEORRES) must equal 'Y', when Inclusion/Exclusion Category (IECAT) is 'EXCLUSION'.

Error Message: Inconsistent values for IEORRES/IECAT
Description: I/E Criterion Original Result (IEORRES) must equal 'N', when Inclusion/Exclusion Category (IECAT) is 'INCLUSION'.

Error Message: Both --DOSE and --DOSTXT values are populated
Description: Only one of Dose (--DOSE) or Dose Description (--DOSTXT) variables must be populated on the same record.

Error Message: Invalid value for QLABEL
Description: Qualifier Variable Label (QLABEL) value may have up to 40 characters.

Error Message: Non-unique value for ETCD within ELEMENT
Description: Element Code (ETCD) must have a unique value for a given value of Description of Element (ELEMENT) within the domain.

Error Message: Unexpected value for IDVAR/IDVARVAL
Description: Both Identifying Variable (IDVAR) and Identifying Variable Value (IDVARVAL) should not be populated, when relating information to the Demographics (DM) domain.

Error Message: Non-unique value for TAETORD within ARMCD
Description: Order of Element within Arm (TAETORD) must have a unique value for a given value of Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) within the domain.

Error Message: Unexpected value for ARMCD variable
Description: Records for subjects who failed a screening or were not assigned to study treatment (ARMCD is 'SCRNFAIL' or 'NOTASSGN') should not be included in the Trial Arms (TA) or Trial Visits (TV) datasets.

Error Message: Duplicate VISITNUM
Description: The value of Visit Number (VISITNUM) variable should be unique for each record within a subject.

Error Message: Missing MB dataset, when MS dataset is present
Description: Microbiology Specimen (MB) dataset should be included, when a Microbiology Susceptibility Test (MS) dataset is present.

Error Message: AESER is not 'Y', when AESOD equals 'Y'
Description: Serious Event (AESER) variable value is expected to be 'Y', when Occurred with Overdose (AESOD) variable value equals 'Y'.

Error Message: Dataset is not present in define.xml
Description: Datasets included in study data must be described in the data definition document (define.xml).

Error Message: Duplicate ETCD value
Description: The value of Element Code (ETCD) variable must be unique within Trial Elements (TE) domain.

Error Message: Missing RDOMAIN value, when IDVAR is populated
Description: Value of Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN) variable must be populated, when value of Identifying Variable (IDVAR) variable is populated.

Error Message: IDVARVAL value is populated, when RELTYPE values is populated
Description: Variable Value (IDVARVAL) variable value should not be populated, when Relationship Type (RELTYPE) variable value is populated.

Error Message: USUBJID value is populated, when RELTYPE values is populated
Description: Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variable value should not be populated, when Relationship Type (RELTYPE) variable value is populated.

Error Message: Duplicate ELEMENT value
Description: The value of Element (Description of Element) variable must be unique within Trial Elements (TE) domain.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --PARM within --PARMCD
Description: All values of a Parameter (--PARM) variables should be the same for a given value of a Parameter Short Name (--PARMCD) variables.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --PARMCD within --PARM
Description: All values of a Parameter Short Name (--PARMCD) variables should be the same for a given value of a Parameter (--PARM) variables.

Error Message: Dataset is greater than 5 GB in size
Description: Datasets greater than 5 gigabytes (GB) in size should be split into smaller datasets no larger than 5 GB.

Error Message: Missing IDVAR value, when RDOMAIN value is provided
Description: Value of Identifying Variable (IDVAR) variable must be populated, when Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN) variable value is provided, with the only exception of 'DM' value for RDOMAIN.

Error Message: Variable prohibited for use in SDTM
Description: Variables described in IG as inappropriate for usage must be not included in the dataset.

Error Message: Variable which can be used only in SEND
Description: Variables designed only for SEND pre-clinical studies must be not included in the SDTM dataset.

Error Message: Variable not recommended for use
Description: Variables described in IG as not recommended for usage should be not included in the dataset.

Error Message: Model permissible variable added into standard domain
Description: SDTM model variable may be added into standard domains according its domain general class, if there are no restrictions on their usage specified in IG.

Error Message: Regulatory Expected variable not found
Description: Variables requested by the relevant regulatory agency in policy documents should be included in the dataset. E.g., EPOCH.

Error Message: Permissible variable with missing value for all records
Description: Permissible variable should not be present in domain, when the variable has missing value for all records in the dataset.

Error Message: Variable is in wrong order within domain
Description: Order of variables should reflect the order of the variables in the SDTM Model. Variables for the three general observation classes must be ordered with Identifiers first, followed by the Topic, Qualifier, and Timing variables. Within each role, variables must be ordered as shown in SDTM: Tables 2.2.1, 2.2.2, 2.2.3, 2.2.4, and 2.2.5.

Error Message: Variable length is too long for actual data
Description: Variable length should be assigned based on actual stored data to minimize file size. Datasets should be re-sized to the maximum length of actual data used prior to splitting.

Error Message: Missing --DY variable, when --DTC variable is present
Description: Collection Study Day (--DY) variable should be included into dataset, when Collection Study Date/Time (--DTC) variable is present.

Error Message: --DY variable value is not populated
Description: Collection Study Day (--DY) variable value should be populated, when Collection Study Date/Time (--DTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Error Message: --DY variable value is imputed
Description: Collection Study Day (--DY) variable value should not be imputed. It may be only populated, when both Collection Study Date/Time (--DTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided and both of them include complete date part.

Error Message: Incorrect value for --DY variable
Description: Collection Study Day (--DY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --DY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) +1 if --DTC is on or after RFSTDTC; --DY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) if --DTC precedes RFSTDTC.

Error Message: Missing --STDY variable, when --STDTC variable is present
Description: Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable should be included into dataset, when Start Study Date/Time (--STDTC) variable is present.

Error Message: --STDY variable value is not populated
Description: Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable value should be populated, when Start Study Date (--STDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Error Message: --STDY variable value is imputed
Description: Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable value should be not be imputed. It may be only populated, when both Start Study Date/Time (--STDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Error Message: Incorrect value for --STDY variable
Description: Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --STDY = (date portion of --STDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) +1 if --STDTC is on or after RFSTDTC; --STDY = (date portion of --STDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) if --STDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

Error Message: Missing --ENDY variable, when --ENDTC variable is present
Description: Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable should be included into dataset, when End Study Date/Time (--ENDTC) variable is present.

Error Message: --ENDY variable value is not populated
Description: Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable value should be populated, when End Study Date/Time (--ENDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Error Message: --ENDY variable value is imputed
