Description: Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable value should not be imputed. It may be only populated, when both End Study Date/Time (--ENDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Error Message: Incorrect value for --ENDY variable
Description: Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --ENDY = (date portion of --ENDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) +1 if --ENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC; --ENDY = (date portion of --ENDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) if --ENDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

Error Message: Invalid dataset name for split domain
Description: Split datasets must not have name of original domain. E.g., lbhm.xpt is a valid name, when lb.xpt is not a valid dataset name for split domain.

Error Message: High risk of truncated value for --TERM variable
Description: SAS v5 export format has a limitation on variables length up to 200 characters. If collected value was more than 200 characters, then SUPPQUAL dataset should be used to store additional 200+ characters. Variable QNAM should have --TERM1, ---TERM2, etc. values for those records. Value splitting should be performed between words or numbers. See SDTM IG #4.1.5.3.2 for details. This risk-assessment check is triggered based on assumption that if original value was truncated, then the actual data value length is exactly 200 characters.

Error Message: No Treatment Emergent info for Adverse Event
Description: A treatment-emergent flag should be included in SUPPAE according to the FDA business rule that states, 'A treatment-emergent flag should be submitted.'

Error Message: Missing --CAT value, when --SCAT value is populated
Description: Value for Category (--CAT) variable should be populated, when value for Subcategory (--SCAT) variable is populated.

Error Message: Missing --CAT variable, when --SCAT variable is present
Description: Category (--CAT) variable should be included into dataset, when Subcategory (--SCAT) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --ENTPT variable, when --ENRTPT variable is present
Description: End Reference Time Point (--ENTPT) variable must be included into the domain, when End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --ENRTPT variable, when --ENTPT variable is present
Description: End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) variable must be included into the domain, when End Relative Time Point (--ENTPT) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --STTPT variable, when --STRTPT variable is present
Description: Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) variable must be included into the domain, when Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --STRTPT variable, when --STTPT variable is present
Description: Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) variable must be included into the domain, when Start Relative Time Point (--STTPT) variable is present.

Error Message: EPOCH variable is populated, when DSCAT equals 'PROTOCOL MILESTONE'
Description: Epoch (EPOCH) variable value should not be populated, when Category for Disposition Event (DSCAT) variable value equals 'PROTOCOL MILESTONE'.

Error Message: Missing AE dataset
Description: Adverse Events (AE) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Missing LB dataset
Description: Lab Test Results (LB) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Missing VS dataset
Description: Vital Signs (VS) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Missing EX dataset
Description: Exposure (EX) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Missing DS dataset
Description: Disposition (DS) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Missing SE dataset
Description: Subject Elements (SE) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Missing TA dataset
Description: Trial Arms (TA) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Missing TE dataset
Description: Trial Elements (TE) dataset should be included in every submission.

Error Message: Value for --BODSYS not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS) variable must be populated using a System Organ Class of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Error Message: Value for --BODSYS is in incorrect case
Description: Case for Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS) variable must follow MedDRA sentence  case and be populated using a System Organ Class of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-sensitive).

Error Message: Missing TS dataset
Description: Trial Summary (TS) dataset must be included in every submission.

Error Message: Inconsistent variable length within split datasets
Description: Split datasets should have matching variable lengths for future merges. Datasets should be resized to the maximum length used prior to splitting.

Error Message: Duplicate records
Description: The structure of Findings class domains should be one record per Finding Result per subject. No Finding Result with the same Test Short Name (--TESTCD) and the same Qualifier variables at the same timepoint for the same Subject (USUBJID) are expected.

Error Message: Neither --STDTC, --DTC nor  --STDY are populated
Description: At least one value of three variables Start Date/Time (--STDTC), Collection Date/Time (--DTC) or Start Study Day (--STDY) should be populated.

Error Message: Inappropriate usage of variables in CO domain, when comment is a child record of another domain
Description: In the Comments (CO) domain, the following Identifier and Timing variables are Permissible and may be populated as appropriate when comments are not related to other domain records (i.e., RDOMAIN and IDVAR variable values are not populated): COGRPID, COREFID, COSPID, VISIT, VISITNUM, VISITDY, TAETORD, CODY, COTPT, COTPTNUM, COELTM, COTPTREF, CORFTDTC.

Error Message: Comments in SUPPQUAL domain
Description: Comments should be stored in Comments (CO) domain, rather than be put into Supplemental Qualifier (SUPP--) domains.

Error Message: Neither AGE nor AGETXT values are populated
Description: Value for Age (AGE) or Age Range (AGETXT) variables should be populated for all subjects. The only exception for SDTM is for Screen Failures (ARMCD=SCRNFAIL) and Not Assigned (ARMCD=NOTASSGN) subjects, or subjects with ARMCD=null.  There are no exceptions for SEND.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRESN
Description: Standardized Result in Numeric Format (--STRESN) variable value should be populated, when Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value represents a numeric value.

Error Message: --ORRES value is populated, when --STAT is 'NOT DONE'
Description: Value of Original Result (--ORRES) variable is expected to be missing, when observation was not performed (Status (--STAT) is 'NOT DONE').

Error Message: Missing value for --REASND, when --STAT is 'NOT DONE'
Description: Value of Reason Not Done (--REASND) variable should be populated, when Status (--STAT) variable value is 'NOT DONE'.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for  --ELTM within --TPT, --TPTREF and/or VISITNUM
Description: All values of Planned Elapsed Time (--ELTM) variable should be the same for a given value of Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable, Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) and/or Visit Number (VISITNUM)

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --TPT within --TPTNUM, --TPTREF, VISITNUM
Description: All values of Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable should be the same for a given value of Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable, Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable, and Visit Number (VISITNUM) variable.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --TPTNUM within --TPT, --TPTREF, VISITNUM
Description: All values of Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable should be the same for a given value of Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable, Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable, and Visit Number (VISITNUM) variable.

Error Message: Invalid value for RELTYPE variable
Description: Relationship Type (RELTYPE)  variable values should be populated with terms 'ONE', 'MANY', when Related Records (RELREC) dataset is used to identify relationships between datasets.

Error Message: Neither AGE nor AGETXT variables are present
Description: At least one of Age (AGE) or Age Text (AGETXT) variables should be included into Demographics (DM) domain.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for QNAM within QLABEL
Description: All values of Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM) should be the same for a given value of Qualifier Variable Label (QLABEL).

Error Message: Missing --STRESC value for Baseline record
Description: A Standard Result value (--STRESC) is expected to be populated for Baseline records (--BLFL='Y').

Error Message: AESER is not 'Y'
Description: Serious Event (AESER) variable value is expected to be 'Y', when either of Seriousness Criteria variables (AESCAN, AESCONG, AESDISAB, AESDTH, AESHOSP, AESLIFE, AESMIE) has value 'Y'.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for ACTARM
Description: A value for Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) must have a unique value for Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) with the domain.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for ACTARMCD
Description: A value for Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) must have a unique value for Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) with the domain.

Error Message: Negative value of Study Day variable
Description: Study Day variables (*DY) value should not be negative in Exposure (EX) datasets.

Error Message: Non-missing value for --ORRES, when --DRVFL='Y'
Description: Character Result/Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) value should be NULL, when Derived Flag (--DRVFL) value is 'Y'.

Error Message: --DRVFL='Y', when --ORRES value is populated
Description: Derived Flag (--DRVFL) variable may be populated only when Result in Original Units (--ORRES) value is NULL and Result in Std. Format (--STRESC) value is populated (result is derived rather than collected).

Error Message: No Details info for AESMIE Adverse Event in SUPPAE domain
Description: When a description of Other Medically Important Serious Adverse Events category is collected on a CRF, sponsors should place the description in the SUPPAE dataset using the standard supplemental qualifier name code AESOSP.

Error Message: MHSTDTC date is after RFSTDTC
Description: The medical history dataset includes the subject's prior history at the start of the trial. Start Date/Time of Medical History Event (MHSTDTC) should be before Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC).

Error Message: Missing --PRESP variable, when --OCCUR variable is present
Description: Pre-specified (--PRESP) variable should be included into dataset, when Occurrence (--OCCUR) variable is present. (--PRESP/Events) Used to indicate whether the event describe by --TERM was pre-specified on a CRF.  Value is Y for pre-specified events, null for spontaneously reported events. (--PRESP/Interventions) Used when a specific intervention is pre-specified on a CRF. Values should be 'Y' or null. (--OCCUR) Used to record whether a pre-specified event occurred when information about the occurrence of a specific event is solicited.

Error Message: Expected variable with missing value for all records
Description: Expected variables may contain some null values, but in most cases will not contain null values for every record. When no data has been collected for an Expected variable, however, a null column must still be included in the dataset, and a comment must be included in the define.xml to state that data was not collected.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for IETEST within IETESTCD
Description: All values of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion (IETEST) should be the same for a given value of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Short Name (IETESTCD).

Error Message: Inconsistent value for IETESTCD within IETEST
Description: All values of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Short Name  (IETESTCD) should be the same for a given value of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion (IETEST).

Error Message: Duplicate records in domain
Description: The structure of Events class domains should be one records per Event per subject. No Events with the same Collected Term (--TERM), Decoded Term (--DECOD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Occurrence (--OCCUR), Location (--LOC), Laterality (--LAT), Directionality (--DIR), Severity (--SEV), Toxicity Grade (--TOXGR), Visit Number (VISITNUM), Visit Day (VISITDY), and Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) values for the same Subject (USUBJID) and the same Start Date (--STDTC) are expected.

Error Message: --STDTC date is after RFPENDTC
Description: Start Date/Time (--STDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of End of Participation (RFPENDTC).

Error Message: --DTC date is after RFPENDTC
Description: Date/Time of Collection (--DTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of End of Participation (RFPENDTC).

Error Message: --ENDTC date is after RFPENDTC
Description: End Date/Time (--ENDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of End of Participation (RFPENDTC).

Error Message: EXSTDTC date is before RFXSTDTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Treatment (EXSTDTC) variable value must be greater than or equal to Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC).

Error Message: EXSTDTC date is after RFXENDTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Treatment (EXSTDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC).

Error Message: EXENDTC date is after RFXENDTC
Description: End Date/Time of Treatment (EXENDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC).

Error Message: RFXSTDTC date is after RFXENDTC
Description: Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC).

Error Message: Missing value for RFXENDTC, when RFXSTDTC is provided
Description: Value for Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC) variable must be populated, when Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable value is provided.

Error Message: Missing value for RFICDTC
Description: Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) variable value should be populated. It would be NULL only in studies not collecting this info.

Error Message: --STRESN does not equal --STRESC
Description: Standardized Result in Numeric Format (--STRESN) variable value should be equal Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value, when Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value represents a numeric value.

Error Message: RFSTDTC is not provided for a treated subject
Description: Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) should be populated for all treated subjects, those where Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) is not equal to 'SCRNFAIL', 'NOTASSGN', 'NOTTRT', or null.

Error Message: Multiple ADDON records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'ADDON' Parameter.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for AGEMAX
Description: TSVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g. P80Y) or null, when TSPARMCD='AGEMAX'.

Error Message: Multiple AGEMAX records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'AGEMAX' Parameter.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for AGEMIN
Description: TSVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g. P80Y) or null, when TSPARMCD='AGEMIN'.

Error Message: Multiple AGEMIN records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'AGEMIN' Parameter.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for LENGTH
Description: TSVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g. P80Y) or null, when TSPARMCD='LENGTH'.

Error Message: Multiple LENGTH records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'LENGTH' Parameter.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for PLANSUB
Description: TSVAL for PLANSUB record must be numeric.

Error Message: Multiple PLANSUB records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'PLANSUB' Parameter.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for RANDOM
Description: TSVAL for RANDOM record must be 'Y' or 'N'.

Error Message: Multiple RANDOM records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'RANDOM' Parameter.

Error Message: Multiple SEXPOP records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'SEXPOP' Parameter.

Error Message: Multiple NARMS records
Description: Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'NARMS' Parameter.

Error Message: Variable value not found in user-defined codelist when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable value must be populated with terms from user-defined value level codelist as specified in define.xml file.

Error Message: Variable value is null when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable value must be populated when value level attribute Mandatory='Yes' as specified in define.xml file.

Error Message: Variable datatype is not %Variable.@Clause.DataType% when value-level condition occurs
Description: Value level datatype must match the datatype described in define.xml.

Error Message: Variable value is longer than defined max length %Variable.@Clause.Length% when value-level condition occurs
Description: Value level length must not exceed the length as specified define.xml.

Error Message: Device is not present in DI domain
Description: All Medical Devices (SPDEVID) must be present in Device Identifier (DI) domain.

Error Message: Missing DEVTYPE Parameter for Device
Description: Device Type (DEVTYPE) Parameter must be populated for each Medical Device in the Device Identifiers (DI) domain.

Error Message: Neither SPDEVID nor USUBJID values are populated
Description: Value for Sponsor Device Identifier (SPDEVID) or Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variables should be populated for all records in Divice In-Use (DU) domain

Error Message: Duplicate value for --SEQ variable
Description: The value of Sequence Number (--SEQ) variable must be unique for each record within a domain and within each combination of Sponsor Device Identifier (SPDEVID) and Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variables' values.

Error Message: Duplicate records in Device Property
Description: There should be one record per device property defined by SPDEVID and DOTESTCD variables

Error Message: --RFTDTC is populated when --TPTREF is not populated
Description: --RFTDTC is defined as the Date/time for a fixed reference time point defined by --TPTREF, therefore --RFTDTC should only be populated when --TPTREF is populated.

Error Message: No Informed Consent Obtained record in DS domain for subject
Description: All subjects should have an Informed Consent record in the Disposition domain.

Error Message: --BODSYS is not populated when --BDSYCD is populated
Description: Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS) must be populated when Body System or Organ Class Code (--BDSYCD) is populated.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --BODSYS within --BDSYCD
Description: All values of Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS) should be the same for a given value of Body System or Organ Class Code (--BDSYCD).

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --BDSYCD within --BODSYS
Description: All values of Body System or Organ Class Code (--BDSYCD) should be the same for a given value of Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS).

Error Message: Missing --TPT variable, when --TPTNUM variable is present
Description: Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable must be included into the domain, when Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --TPTREF variable, when --RFTDTC variable is present
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable must be included into the domain, when Date/Time of Reference Point (--RFTDTC) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --TPTREF variable, when --ELTM variable is present
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable must be included into the domain, when Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref (--ELTM) variable is present.

Error Message: ECDOSE is not greater than 0 when ECOCCUR does not equal 'N' and ECDOSTXT is null
Description: ECDOSE must be greater than zero when ECOCCUR does not equal 'N' , ECSTAT does not equal 'NOT DONE', and ECDOSTXT is null. ECDOSE must not be set to zero (0) as an alternative method for indicating doses not taken, not given, or missed.

Error Message: ECDOSE is not null or greater than 0 when ECOCCUR = 'N'
Description: ECDOSE must either be null when ECOCCUR equals 'N', or ECDOSE must be greater than 0. ECDOSE would be greater than 0 (when ECOCCUR equals N) for records that represent specific dose amounts that are not taken, not given, or missed.

Error Message: EXDOSE does not equal 0 when EXTRT = 'PLACEBO'
Description: EXDOSE must be equal to 0 when EXTRT = 'PLACEBO'.

Error Message: Missing --TPTNUM variable, when --TPT variable is present
Description: Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable must be included into the domain, when Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable is present.

Error Message: --VAMTU is not null when --TRTV is null
Description: Treatment Vehicle Amount Units (--VAMTU) value must be null when Treatment Vehicle Amount (--TRTV) value is null.

Error Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when SS.SSSTRESC = 'DEAD'
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Subject Status (SS) domain with SSSTRESC = 'DEAD'.

Error Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when DD record is present
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Death Details (DD) domain.

Error Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when AE.AEOUT = 'FATAL'
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Adverse Events (AE) domain with AEOUT = 'FATAL'.

Error Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when AE.AESDTH = 'Y'
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Adverse Events (AE) domain with AESDTH = 'Y'.

Error Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when DS.DSDECOD = 'DEATH'
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Disposition (DS) domain with DSDECOD = 'DEATH'.

Error Message: RFSTDTC is populated for subject who did not receive treatment
Description: RFSTDTC must be null when actual arm indicates that the subject is a screen failure ('Screen Failure'), was not assigned to an arm ('Not Assigned'), was not treated ('NOTTRT'), or actual arm is null. This rule applies to studies where RFSTDTC is associated with a treatment date.

Error Message: Invalid value for SETCD
Description: The value of Set Code (SETCD) should be no more than 8 characters in length.

Error Message: TSVCDVER is null when Reference Terminology is versioned
Description: The Version of the Reference Terminology variable (TSVCDVER) should be populated with the version number of the Reference Terminology, when that Reference Terminology is versioned.

Error Message: SSDTC is not greater than or equal to DTHDTC, when SSSTRESC = 'DEAD'
Description: Subject Status Date/Time of Assessment (SSDTC) must be greater than or equal to Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) when the subject's status is 'DEAD'.

Error Message: SSDTC is not greater than or equal to DSSTDTC, when SSSTRESC = 'DEAD'
Description: Subject Status Date/Time of Assessment (SSDTC) must be greater than or equal to Start Date/Time of Disposition Event (DSSTDTC) when the subject's status is 'DEAD'.

Error Message: MBRESCAT is null when MBTESTCD = 'ORGANISM'
Description: MBRESCAT is expected to be populated in all records where a microorganism has been identified (MBTESTCD = 'ORGANISM'), excluding records where MBSTRESC equals 'NO GROWTH' or MBMETHOD equals 'GRAM STAIN'.

Error Message: IDVAR equals --SEQ when IDVARVAL is null and USUBJID is null
Description: When the RELREC dataset is used to identify relationships between datasets (in which case USUBJID and IDVARVAL are left null), instead of relating individual records, --SEQ cannot be used for IDVAR because --SEQ only has meaning within a subject within a dataset, not across datasets.

Error Message: QEVAL is null when QORIG equals 'ASSIGNED'
Description: For subjective data (when QORIG='ASSIGNED'), QEVAL should be populated and the value should reflect the role of the person or institution assigning the value.

Error Message: ETCD equals 'UNPLAN' when SEUPDES is null
Description: When the Description of Unplanned Element (SEUPDES) is not populated, the Element Code (ETCD) should not be equal to 'UNPLAN'.

Error Message: Invalid value for TAETORD
Description: Planned Order of Element within Arm (TAETORD) variable value must be an integer.

Error Message: TSVCDREF is null when TSVCDVER is populated
Description: The Name of the Reference Terminology (TSVCDREF) must be populated when the Version of the Reference Terminology (TSVCDVER) is populated.

Error Message: TSVAL is not between 0 and 1, when TSPARMCD = 'RANDQT'
Description: For the trial summary parameter Randomization Quotient (TSPARMCD = 'RANDQT'), the value must always be a number between 0 and 1, with some cases where the ratio might be equal to 1.

Error Message: Missing PC dataset, when PP dataset is present
Description: Pharmacokinetic Concentrations (PC) dataset should be included, when a Pharmacokinetic Parameters(PP) dataset is present.

Error Message: The combination of ELEMENT, TESTRL TEENRL, and TEDUR is not unique for each ETCD
Description: The combination of Description of Element (ELEMENT), Rule for Start of Element (TESTRL), Rule for End of Element (TEENRL), and Planned Duration of Element (TEDUR) should be unique for each Element Code (ETCD).

Error Message: --TESTCD equals 'OTHER'
Description: Test Code variables (--TESTCD) should not be populated with values of 'OTHER'.

Error Message: --TRT equals 'OTHER'
Description: Name of Treatment variables (--TRT) should not be populated with values of 'OTHER'.

Error Message: --TERM equals 'OTHER'
Description: Reported Term variables (--TERM) should not be populated with values of 'OTHER'.

Error Message: --TESTCD equals 'MULTIPLE'
Description: Test Code variables (--TESTCD) should not be populated with values of 'MULTIPLE'.

Error Message: --TRT equals 'MULTIPLE'
Description: Name of Treatment variables (--TRT) should not be populated with values of 'MULTIPLE'.

Error Message: --TERM equals 'MULTIPLE'
Description: Reported Term variables (--TERM) should not be populated with values of 'MULTIPLE'.

Error Message: Inconsistent value for TSVALCD within TSVAL
Description: Parameter Value Code (TSVALCD) and Parameter Value (TSVAL) should have a one-to-one relationship.

Error Message: ECDOSTXT is null when ECDOSE is null and ECOCCUR does not equal 'N'
Description: Dose Description (ECDOSTXT) should be populated when Dose (ECDOSE) is null, ECOCCUR does not equal 'N', and ECSTAT does not equal 'NOT DONE'.

Error Message: --TOX variable is present when --TOXGR variable is missing
Description: Toxicity (--TOX) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Toxicity Grade (--TOXGR) variable is missing.

Error Message: --TPTREF variable is present when --ELTM, --TPTNUM, and --TPT are missing
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref (--ELTM) variable, Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable, and Planned Time Point (--TPT) variable are missing.

Error Message: --LAT variable is present when --LOC variable is missing
Description: Laterality (--LAT) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Location (--LOC) variable is missing.

Error Message: --PORTOT variable is present when --LOC variable is missing
Description: Portion or Totality (--PORTOT) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Location (--LOC) variable is missing.

Error Message: --DIR variable is present when --LOC variable is missing
Description: Directionality (--DIR) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Location (--LOC) variable is missing.

Error Message: IETESTCD is not unique within TIVERS
Description: A value of Incl/Excl Criterion Short Name (IETESTCD) must be unique within a version of inclusion/exclusion criteria (TIVERS).

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --DECOD within --PTCD
Description: All values of Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD) should be the same for a given value of Preferred Term Code (--PTCD).

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --PTCD within --DECOD
Description: All values of Preferred Term Code (--PTCD) should be the same for a given value of Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD).

Error Message: Missing value for --DECOD, when --PTCD is populated
Description: Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD) should be populated when Preferred Term Code (--PTCD) is populated.

Error Message: Multiple disposition events for the same EPOCH
Description: If multiple disposition events are reported for an EPOCH, the sponsor should identify a primary reason and use that to populate DSTERM and DSDECOD. Additional reasons should be submitted in SUPPDS.

Error Message: Missing value for --ENRTPT, when --ENTPT is populated
Description: End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) must be populated when End Reference Time Point (--ENTPT) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRTPT, when --STTPT is populated
Description: Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) must be populated when Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) is populated.

Error Message: --REASND variable is present when --PRESP variable is missing
Description: Reason Not Done (--REASND) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Pre-specified (--PRESP) variable is missing.

Error Message: --STAT variable is present when --PRESP variable is missing
Description: Completion Status (--STAT) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Pre-specified (--PRESP) variable is missing.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for ADDON parameter
Description: TSVAL for ADDON record must be 'Y' or 'N'.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for ADAPT parameter
Description: TSVAL for ADAPT record must be 'Y' or 'N'.

Error Message: TSVAL is populated with a value from the ISO 21090 null flavor codelist
Description: TSVAL should not be populated with a value from the ISO 21090 null flavor codelist, or synonyms of the values. The TSVALNF variable should be used to capture these values, not TSVAL.

Error Message: LBTOXGR is not a numeric value when a numeric scale is used.
Description: When a numeric scale is used (Grade 1, Grade 2, etc.), LBTOXGR should only contain the number.

Error Message: No timing variables are present in dataset
Description: All domains based on the general observation classes (Interventions, Events, Findings) should have at least one Timing variable present.

Error Message: Invalid value for DOMAIN variable
Description: The value of DOMAIN should be no more than 2 characters in length, excluding Associated Persons domains.

Error Message: Invalid value for TDSTOFF variable
Description: Offset from the Anchor (TDSTOFF) variable value must be either 0, ISO 8601 format for duration (e.g. P80Y), or null.

Error Message: The TDIGRP Trial Summary Parameter is not provided with TSVAL equal to null, when HLTSUBJI parameter equals 'Y'
Description: When the study population is healthy subjects (TSPARMCD = 'HLTSUBJI' and TSVAL = 'Y'), the Diagnosis Group parameter should be provided with a null Parameter Value (TSVAL should be null when TSPARMCD = 'TDIGRP').

Error Message: TSVAL is missing for the TDIGRP Trial Summary Parameter, when HLTSUBJI parameter equals 'N'
Description: When the study population is not healthy subjects (TSPARMCD = 'HLTSUBJI' and TSVAL = 'N'), the Diagnosis Group parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'TDIGRP').

Error Message: TSVAL is missing for the CURTRT Trial Summary Parameter, when ADDON parameter equals 'Y'
Description: When test product is added to existing treatment (TSPARMCD = 'ADDON' and TSVAL = 'Y'), the Current Therapy or Treatment parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'CURTRT').

Error Message: TSVAL is missing for the TRT Trial Summary Parameter, when STYPE parameter equals 'INTERVENTIONAL'
Description: When the study type is interventional (TSPARMCD = 'STYPE' and TSVAL = 'INTERVENTIONAL'), the Investigational Therapy or Treatment parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'TRT').

Error Message: TSVAL is missing for the INTMODEL Trial Summary Parameter, when STYPE parameter equals 'INTERVENTIONAL'
Description: When the study type is interventional (TSPARMCD = 'STYPE' and TSVAL = 'INTERVENTIONAL'), the Intervention Model parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'INTMODEL').

Error Message: TSVAL is missing for the INTTYPE Trial Summary Parameter, when STYPE parameter equals 'INTERVENTIONAL'
Description: When the study type is interventional (TSPARMCD = 'STYPE' and TSVAL = 'INTERVENTIONAL'), the Intervention Type parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'INTTYPE').

Error Message: TSVAL is missing for the PCLAS Trial Summary Parameter, when STYPE parameter equals 'INTERVENTIONAL'
Description: When the study type is interventional (TSPARMCD = 'STYPE' and TSVAL = 'INTERVENTIONAL'), the Pharmacologic Class parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'PCLAS').

Error Message: Missing EPOCH value, when DSCAT is 'DISPOSITION EVENT'
Description: Epoch (EPOCH) variable should be provided, when Category for Disposition Event (DSCAT) equals 'DISPOSITION EVENT'.

Error Message: DSDECOD is not 'COMPLETED', when DSTERM='COMPLETED'
Description: When Reported Term for the Disposition Event (DSTERM) is 'COMPLETED', Standardized Disposition Term (DSDECOD) should have the same value 'COMPLETED'.

Error Message: DSDECOD is not the same as DSTERM, when DSCAT='PROTOCOL MILESTONE'
Description: Reported Term for the Disposition Event (DSTERM) and Standardized Disposition Term (DSDECOD) should contain the same value, when Category for Disposition Event (DSCAT) is 'PROTOCOL MILESTONE'.

Error Message: Missing 'DEATH' record for subject in DS domain
Description: All subjects who have Death records (SSSTRESC = 'DEAD') in Survival Status (SS) domain should also have death records (DSDECOD='DEATH') in Disposition (DS) domain.

Error Message: DSSTDTC for DEATH record is not the same as DM.DTHDTC
Description: DEATH records (DSDECOD='DEATH') in the Disposition (DS) domain should have Start Date of Event (DSSTDTC) equal to subject's Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) populated in the Demographics (DM) domain. Subject's Date/Time of Death info should be consistent across all domains.

Error Message: No records for subject are found in DV domain
Description: Subjects who have DSDECOD = 'PROTOCOL VIOLATION' or DSDECOD = 'PROTOCOL DEVIATION' records in the Disposition (DS) domain should have supportive records with details in the Protocol Deviations (DV) domain.

Error Message: --STDTC is before RFICDTC
Description: All records in the Disposition (DS) and Protocol Deviations (DV) domains should have the Start Date/Time of Event (--STDTC) equal to or after a subject's Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) in the Demographics (DM) domain.

Error Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --STAT is null
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Format (--STRESC) value should not be NULL, when Completion Status (--STAT) value is NULL.

Error Message: No Treatment Emergent info for Adverse Event (missing SUPPAE)
Description: A treatment-emergent flag should be included in SUPPAE according to the FDA business rule that states, 'A treatment-emergent flag should be submitted.'

Error Message: Value for COUNTRY not found in ISO 3166
Description: Value for the Country (COUNTRY) variable must be populated using terms found in ISO 3166.

Error Message: Invalid TSVAL value for FCNTRY
Description: TSVAL for FCNTRY record must be a valid term from ISO 3166.

Error Message: Define.xml/dataset variable label mismatch
Description: Variable Label in define.xml must match variable Label in dataset.

Error Message: Define.xml/dataset description mismatch
Description: Dataset Description in define.xml must match dataset Description.

Error Message: RDEVID is not null when RSUBJID is populated
Description: Related Device Identifier (RDEVID) and Related Subject or Pool Identifier (RSUBJID) should not both be populated for the same record.

Error Message: RSUBJID is equal to POOLID
Description: The Related Subject or Pool Identifier (RSUBJID) value should not be equal to Pool Identifier (POOLID).

Error Message: RSUBJID is equal to USUBJID
Description: The Related Subject or Pool Identifier (RSUBJID) value should not be equal to USUBJID.

Error Message: --DY is after --ENDY
Description: Study Day of Observation (--DY) must be less or equal to Study Day of End of Observation (--ENDY)

Error Message: --STDTC is after --DTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Event, Exposure (--STDTC) must be less or equal to Date/Time of Collection(--DTC)

Error Message: AEOUT = NOT RECOVERED/NOT RESOLVED, but an end date is provided
Description: The Outcome of Adverse Event (AEOUT) variable is populated with the value NOT RECOVERED/NOT RESOLVED, however the End Date/Time of Adverse Event (AEENDTC) variable is populated with an end date for the adverse event. If the adverse event has an outcome of NOT RECOVERED/NOT RESOLVED, it is expected that no end date is available.

Error Message: AEOUT = RECOVERED/RESOLVED, but an end date or collected duration is not provided
Description: The Outcome of Adverse Event (AEOUT) variable is populated with the value RECOVERED/RESOLVED, however the End Date/Time of Adverse Event (AEENDTC) or Duration of Adverse Event (AEDUR) variables are null. If the adverse event has an outcome of RECOVERED/RESOLVED, it is expected that an end date or a collected duration be provided.

Error Message: RFICDTC is after RFSTDTC
Description: Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) should not be after Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC).

Error Message: RFICDTC is after RFXSTDTC
Description: Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) should not be after Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC).

Error Message: TRLNKID value does not exist in TU domain
Description: A Link ID (TRLNKID) value for a tumor that is referenced in the Tumor Results (TR) domain for a subject must also be present in the Tumor Identification (TU) domain for that subject.

Error Message: RSLNKID value does not exist in TR domain
Description: A Link ID (RSLNKID) value for a response assessment that is referenced in the Disease Response (RS) domain for a subject must also be present in the Tumor Results (TR) domain for the appropriate measurement records for that subject.

Error Message: RSLNKGRP value does not exist in TR domain
Description: A Link Group (RSLNKGRP) value for a response assessment that is referenced in the Disease Response (RS) domain for a subject must also be present in the Tumor Results (TR) domain for the appropriate measurement records for that subject.

Error Message: Missing EPOCH value, when a start or observation date is provided
Description: The EPOCH variable is not populated, however either a start date or a collection date is provided. The presence of a start date or collection date for a record should allow for the EPOCH variable to be populated. Variables requested by the relevant regulatory agency in policy documents (e.g., EPOCH) should be included in the dataset and populated.

Error Message: EX record is present, when subject is not treated
Description: Subjects that are not treated (ACTARMCD='NOTTRT' or null) should not have any Exposure records. Run-in records (EPOCH='RUN-IN') are excluded from firing for this validation rule.

Error Message: Missing value for RFXSTDTC, when RFXENDTC is provided
Description: Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable must be populated, when Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC)variable value is provided.

Error Message: Missing value for RFXSTDTC, when subject is treated
Description: Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable must be populated, when subject is treated (ACTARMCD is not 'SCRNFAIL', 'NOTTRT', 'NOTASSGN', or null).

Error Message: Value for --DECOD not found in WHODrug dictionary
Description: Value for the Standardized Medication Name (--DECOD) variable must be populated using a Drug Name from the WHO Drug dictionary version specified in the define.xml.

Error Message: Value for --CLAS not found in WHODrug dictionary
Description: Value for the Medication Class (--CLAS) variable must be populated using ATC Text from the WHO Drug dictionary version specified in the define.xml.

Error Message: Value for --CLASCD not found in WHODrug dictionary
Description: Value for the Medication Class Code (--CLASCD) variable must be populated using ATC Code from the WHO Drug dictionary version specified in the define.xml.

Error Message: AEENDTC for fatal AE is not the same as DM.DTHDTC
Description: Fatal Adverse Event records (AEOUT = 'FATAL') in the Adverse Events (AE) domain should have End Date/Time of Adverse Event (AEENDTC) equal to subject's Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) populated in the Demographics (DM) domain. Subject's Date/Time of Death info should be consistent across all domains.

Error Message: Missing values for --STINT and --ENINT variables when --TEST references 'T1 to T2'
Description: Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) and Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) variables should be present and populated when Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST) is over a time interval, 'T1 to T2', where 'T1' is represented by the value in --STINT and 'T2' is represented by the value in --ENINT.

Error Message: Inconsistent STUDYID
Description: Study Identifier (STUDYID) values should be consistent for all subjects in the Demographics (DM) domain for one study.

Error Message: Missing value for --ENINT, when --STINT is provided
Description: Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) should not be NULL, when Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) is populated.

Error Message: Missing value for --STINT, when --ENINT is provided
Description: Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) should not be NULL, when Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) is populated.

Error Message: Duplicate records in domain
Description: The structure of Interventions class domains should be one record per Intervention Episode per subject. No Interventions with the same Treatment (--TRT), Decoded Term (--DECOD), Mood (--MOOD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Route (--ROUTE), Location (--LOC) and Treatment Vehicle (--TRTV) values for the same Subject (USUBJID) with the same Start Date (--STDTC), Planned Time Point Name (--TPT), and Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) are expected.

Error Message: --STRESC does not equal --ORRES when --STRESU is equal to --ORRESU
Description: Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value should be equal to Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) variable value, when variable values are numeric and Standard Units (--STRESU) and Original Units (--ORRESU) are populated with the same units or are null.

Error Message: ARMCD value not present in DM
Description: Arm Code (ARMCD) values defined in Trial Arms (TA) should be assigned to at least one subject (USUBJID) in Demographics (DM).

Error Message: Missing TM dataset, when variable MIDS is present in a dataset
Description: When the Disease Milestone Instance Name (MIDS) variable is used in any dataset, the Trial Disease Milestones (TM) dataset must be present for the study.

Error Message: Missing TM dataset, when variable RELMIDS is present in a dataset
Description: When the Temporal Relation to Milestone Instance (RELMIDS) variable is used in any dataset, the Trial Disease Milestones (TM) dataset must be present for the study.

Error Message: MIDSDTC variable is present when MIDS variable is missing
Description: Disease Milestone Instance Date/Time (MIDSDTC) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Disease Milestone Instance Name (MIDS) variable is missing.

Error Message: ARMNRS is not populated, when ACTARMCD or ACTARM is NULL
Description: When Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD)/Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) are not populated, the Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable must be populated with the reason ACTARMCD/ACTARM are null.

Error Message: ARMNRS is not populated when ARMCD/ARM are not provided
Description: When Planned Arm Code (ARMCD)/Description of Planned Arm (ARM) are not populated, the Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable must be populated with the reason ARMCD/ARM are null.

Error Message: ARMNRS is populated but ARMCD and ACTARMCD are populated
Description: The Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable should only be populated when Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) and Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) are null.

Error Message: ARM is populated, but ARMCD is null, or vice versa
Description: Description of Planned Arm (ARM) must be populated, when Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) is populated, and vice versa.

Error Message: ACTARM is populated, but ACTARMCD is null, or vice versa
Description: Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) must be populated, when Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) is populated, and vice versa.

Error Message: ARMCD/ARM is populated for a subject not assigned to treatment
Description: Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) and Description of Planned Arm (ARM) must not be null for subjects who are not assigned to treatment. This includes Screen Failure subjects and Not Assigned subjects.

Error Message: ACTARMCD/ACTARM is populated for a subject who wasn't treated
Description: Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) and Actual Arm (ACTARM) must be null for subjects who weren't treated. This includes Screen Failure subjects, Not Assigned subjects, and Not Treated subjects.

Error Message: ADSL Population Flags provided in SDTM
Description: ADSL Population Flags, which had standard Supplemental Qualifiers included in previous versions of the SDTMIG (COMPLT, FASFL/FULLSET, ITT, PPROTFL/PPROT, SAFFL/SAFETY, etc.) should no longer be used in SDTM.

Error Message: RFENDTC is populated when ARMNRS is not null
Description: Subject Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC) should be null for screen failures or unassigned subjects. Therefore, when the Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable is populated, RFENDTC should be null.

Error Message: Multiple disposition events for the same DSSCAT and EPOCH
Description: There should be at most one disposition event record per subject per Subcategory for Disposition Event (DSSCAT) per Epoch. If multiple disposition events are reported for a Subcategory for DSSCAT and EPOCH, the sponsor should identify a primary reason and use that to populate DSTERM and DSDECOD. Additional reasons should be submitted in SUPPDS.

Error Message: SMSTDTC is null
Description: Start Date/Time of Milestone (SMSTDTC) should not be null. The start date/time of the Disease Milestone is the critical date/time, and must be populated.

Error Message: --STREFC is null when --ORREF is populated
Description: Reference Result in Standard Format (--STREFC) should be populated when Reference Result in Original Units (--ORREF) is populated.

Error Message: --STREFN is null when --STREFC is populated
Description: Numeric Reference Result in Std Units (--STREFN) should be populated when Reference Result in Standard Format (--STREFC) is populated.

Error Message: --ORRES is null when --LOBXFL = 'Y' (and --DRVFL is null)
Description: Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) should be populated when Last Observation Before Exposure Flag (--LOBXFL) is set to 'Y', unless the record is derived (--DRVFL = 'Y').

Error Message: --STRESC is null when --LOBXFL = 'Y'
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Format (--STRESC) should be populated when Last Observation Before Exposure Flag (--LOBXFL) is set to 'Y'.

Error Message: RFSTDTC is populated for subject who did not receive treatment
Description: RFSTDTC must be null when the Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable is populated (excluding values of UNPLANNED TREATMENT), which indicates that the subject did not receive treatment.

Error Message: No Disposition record found for subject
Description: All Demographics (DM) subjects (USUBJID) should have at least one record in the Disposition (DS) domain with only possible exceptions to subjects who did not receive treatment (ACTARMCD is null).

Error Message: RFENDTC is populated for subject who did not receive treatment
Description: RFENDTC must be null when actual arm indicates that the subject is a screen failure ('Screen Failure'), was not assigned to an arm ('Not Assigned'), or was not treated ('NOTTRT') (or null). This rule applies to studies where RFENDTC is associated with a treatment date.

Error Message: RFENDTC is not provided for a treated subject
Description: Subject Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC) should be populated for all treated subjects, those where Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) is not equal to 'SCRNFAIL', 'NOTASSGN' or 'NOTTRT' (or null).

Error Message: No records for SCREEN FAILURE subject are found in IE domain
Description: All subjects with Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) equal to 'SCREEN FAILURE' should have records in the Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria Not Met (IE) domain.

Error Message: ETCD value not present in TA
Description: Element Code (ETCD) values defined in Trial Elements (TE) should be assigned for at least one Arm Code (ARMCD) in Trial Arms (Trial Arms).

Error Message: ETCD value not present in SE
Description: Element Code (ETCD) values defined in Trial Elements (TE) should be assigned to at least one subject (USUBJID) in Subject Elements (SE).

Error Message: No subject identifier variables are populated
Description: At least one of the following subject identifier variables must be populated for each record: Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID), Associated Persons Identifier (APID), Sponsor Device Identifier (SPDEVID), or Pool Identifier (POOLID).

Error Message: Incorrect value for --XDY variable
Description: Day of Obs Relative to Exposure (--XDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --XDY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFXSTDTC) +1 if --DTC is on or after RFXSTDTC; --XDY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFXSTDTC) if --DTC precedes RFXSTDTC.

Error Message: Incorrect value for --XSTDY variable
Description: Start Day of Obs Relative to Exposure (--XSTDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --XSTDY = (date portion of --STDTC) - (date portion of RFXSTDTC) +1 if --STDTC is on or after RFXSTDTC; --XSTDY = (date portion of --STDTC) - (date portion of RFXSTDTC) if --STDTC precedes RFXSTDTC.

Error Message: Incorrect value for --XENDY variable
Description: End Day of Obs Relative to Exposure (--XENDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --XENDY = (date portion of --ENDTC) - (date portion of RFXSTDTC) +1 if --ENDTC is on or after RFXSTDTC; --XENDY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFXSTDTC) if --ENDTC precedes RFXSTDTC.

Error Message: Incorrect value for --CHDY variable
Description: Day of Obs Rel to Challenge Agent (--CHDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --CHDY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFCSTDTC) +1 if --DTC is on or after RFCSTDTC; --CHDY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFCSTDTC) if --DTC precedes RFCSTDTC.

Error Message: Incorrect value for --CHSTDY variable
Description: Start Day of Obs Rel to Challenge Agent (--CHSTDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --CHSTDY = (date portion of --STDTC) - (date portion of RFCSTDTC) +1 if --STDTC is on or after RFCSTDTC; --CHSTDY = (date portion of --STDTC) - (date portion of RFCSTDTC) if --STDTC precedes RFCSTDTC.

Error Message: Incorrect value for --CHENDY variable
Description: End Day of Obs Rel to Challenge Agent (--CHENDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --CHENDY = (date portion of --ENDTC) - (date portion of RFCSTDTC) +1 if --ENDTC is on or after RFCSTDTC; --CHENDY = (date portion of --ENDTC) - (date portion of RFCSTDTC) if --ENDTC precedes RFCSTDTC.

Error Message: --XDY variable value is imputed
Description: Day of Obs relative to Exposure (--XDY) variable value should not be imputed. It may only be populated, when both Date/Time of Collection (--DTC) and Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variables values are provided and both of them include complete date parts.

Error Message: --XSTDY variable value is imputed
Description: Start Day of Obs relative to Exposure (--XSTDY) variable value should not be imputed. It may only be populated, when both Start Date/Time of Observation (--STDTC) and Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variables values are provided and both of them include complete date parts.

Error Message: --XENDY variable value is imputed
Description: End Day of Obs Relative to Exposure (--XENDY) variable value should not be imputed. It may only be populated, when both End Date/Time of Observation (--ENDTC) and Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variables values are provided and both of them include complete date parts.

Error Message: --CHDY variable value is imputed
Description: Day of Obs Rel to Challenge Agent (--CHDY) variable value should not be imputed. It may only be populated, when both Date/Time of Collection (--DTC) and Date/Time of First Challenge Agent Admin (RFCSTDTC) variables values are provided and both of them include complete date parts.

Error Message: --CHSTDY variable value is imputed
Description: Start Day of Obs Rel to Challenge Agent (--CHSTDY) variable value should not be imputed. It may only be populated, when both Start Date/Time of Observation (--STDTC) and Date/Time of First Challenge Agent Admin (RFCSTDTC) variables values are provided and both of them include complete date parts.

Error Message: --CHENDY variable value is imputed
Description: End Day of Obs Rel to Challenge Agent (--CHENDY) variable value should not be imputed. It may only be populated, when both End Date/Time of Observation (--ENDTC) and Date/Time of First Challenge Agent Admin (RFCSTDTC) variables values are provided and both of them include complete date parts.

Error Message: --XDY variable value is not populated
Description: Day of Obs Relative to Exposure (--XDY) variable value should be populated, when Date/Time of Collection (--DTC) and Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date parts.

Error Message: --XSTDY variable value is not populated
Description: Start Day of Obs Relative to Exposure (--XSTDY) variable value should be populated, when Start Date/Time of Observation (--STDTC) and Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date parts.

Error Message: --XENDY variable value is not populated
Description: End Day of Obs Relative to Exposure (--XENDY) variable value should be populated, when End Date/Time of Observation (--ENDTC) and Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date parts.

Error Message: --CHDY variable value is not populated
Description: Day of Obs Rel to Challenge Agent (--CHDY) variable value should be populated, when Date/Time of Collection (--DTC) and Date/Time of First Challenge Agent Admin (RFCSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date parts.

Error Message: --CHSTDY variable value is not populated
Description: Start Day of Obs Rel to Challenge Agent (--CHSTDY) variable value should be populated, when Start Date/Time of Observation (--STDTC) and Date/Time of First Challenge Agent Admin (RFCSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date parts.

Error Message: --CHENDY variable value is not populated
Description: End Day of Obs Rel to Challenge Agent (--CHENDY) variable value should be populated, when End Date/Time of Observation (--ENDTC) and Date/Time of First Challenge Agent Admin (RFCSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date parts.

Error Message: AGSTDTC date is before RFCSTDTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Agent (AGSTDTC) variable value must be greater than or equal to Date/Time of First Challenge Agent Admin (RFCSTDTC).

Error Message: AGSTDTC date is after RFCENDTC
Description: Start Date/Time of Agent (AGSTDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Challenge Agent Admin (RFCENDTC).

Error Message: AGENDTC date is after RFCENDTC
Description: End Date/Time of Agent (AGENDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Challenge Agent Admin (RFCENDTC).

Error Message: RFCSTDTC date is after RFCENDTC
Description: Date/Time of First Challenge Agent Admin (RFCSTDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Challenge Agent Admin (RFCENDTC).

Error Message: Missing value for RFCENDTC, when RFCSTDTC is provided
Description: Value for Date/Time of Last Challenge Agent Admin  (RFXENDTC) variable must be populated, when Date/Time of First Challenge Agent Admin (RFXSTDTC) variable value is provided.

Error Message: Missing value for RFCSTDTC, when RFCENDTC is provided
Description: Date/Time of First Challenge Agent Admin (RFCSTDTC) variable must be populated, when Date/Time of Last Challenge Agent Admin (RFXENDTC) variable value is provided.

Error Message: Missing CAGTCAT Challenge Agent Parameter
Description: 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) record must be populated in Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain.

Error Message: Missing CAGTSUPA Challenge Agent Parameter
Description: 'Challenge Agent Supplier Address' (CAGTSUPA) record must be populated in Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain.

Error Message: Missing CAGTSUPN Challenge Agent Parameter
Description: 'Challenge Agent Supplier Name' (CAGTSUPN) record must be populated in Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain.

Error Message: Missing MCCATIND Challenge Agent Parameter
Description: 'Multiple Challenge Agent Category Ind' (MCCATIND) record must be populated in Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain.

Error Message: Missing MCSCTIND Challenge Agent Parameter
Description: 'Multiple Challenge Agent Same Cat Ind' (MCSCTIND) record must be populated in Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain.

Error Message: Missing BAMTIDCD Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'BIOLOGICAL'
Description: 'Biological Agent Material Ident Code' (BAMTIDCD) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'BIOLOGICAL'.

Description: 'Bio Ag Work Bank/Primary Stock Char Ind' (BWBPSIND) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'BIOLOGICAL'.

Error Message: Missing BABIOVRN Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'BIOLOGICAL'
Description: 'Biological Agent Biovar Name' (BABIOVRN) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'BIOLOGICAL'.

Error Message: Missing BACAT Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'BIOLOGICAL'
Description: 'Biological Agent Category' (BACAT) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'BIOLOGICAL'.

Error Message: Missing BACOAIND Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'BIOLOGICAL'
Description: 'Biological Agent CoA Indicator' (BACOAIND) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'BIOLOGICAL'.

Error Message: Missing BAENGIND Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'BIOLOGICAL'
Description: 'Biological Agent Engineered Indicator' (BAENGIND) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'BIOLOGICAL'.

Error Message: Missing BAGENSPC Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'BIOLOGICAL'
Description: 'Biological Agent Genus and Species' (BAGENSPC) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'BIOLOGICAL'.

Error Message: Missing BAMBSSDS Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'BIOLOGICAL'
Description: 'Bio Master Bank or Seed Stock Dir Supp' (BAMBSSDS) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'BIOLOGICAL'.

Error Message: Missing BANSIND Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'BIOLOGICAL'
Description: 'Biological Agent Nucleotide Sequence Ind' (BANSIND) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'BIOLOGICAL'.

Error Message: Missing BANSLOC Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'BIOLOGICAL'
Description: 'Biological Agent Nucleotide Sequence Loc' (BANSLOC) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'BIOLOGICAL'.

Error Message: Missing BASEROVN Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'BIOLOGICAL'
Description: 'Biological Agent Serovar Name' (BASEROVN) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'BIOLOGICAL'.

Error Message: Missing BASTRNN Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'BIOLOGICAL'
Description: 'Biological Agent Strain Name' (BASTRNN) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'BIOLOGICAL'.

Error Message: Missing CHAMCIND Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'CHEMICAL'
Description: 'Chemical Ag Metabolite Causes Injury Ind' (CHAMCIND) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'CHEMICAL'.

Error Message: Missing CHAGCAS Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'CHEMICAL'
Description: 'Chemical Agent CAS Number' (CHAGCAS) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'CHEMICAL'.

Error Message: Missing CHAGNAM Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'CHEMICAL'
Description: 'Chemical Agent Name' (CHAGNAM) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'CHEMICAL'.

Error Message: Missing CHCOAIND Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'CHEMICAL'
Description: 'Chemical Agent CoA Indicator' (CHCOAIND) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'CHEMICAL'.

Error Message: Missing CHMTIDCD Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'CHEMICAL'
Description: 'Chemical Agent Material Ident Code' (CHMTIDCD) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'CHEMICAL'.

Error Message: Missing RNAIOTYP Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'
Description: 'Rad/Nuc Agent Ionizing Radiation Type' (RNAIOTYP) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'.

Error Message: Missing RNAISBS Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'
Description: 'Rad/Nuc Agent Irrad Source Beam Strength' (RNAISBS) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'.

Error Message: Missing RNAMFIND Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'
Description: 'Rad/Nuc Agent Mixed Field Indicator' (RNAMFIND) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'.

Error Message: Missing RNARADSN Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'
Description: 'Rad/Nuc Agent Radioisotope Species Name' (RNARADSN) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'.

Error Message: Missing RNASRC Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'
Description: 'Rad/Nuc Agent Source' (RNASRC) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'.

Error Message: Missing BIRRMDL Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'
Description: 'Body Irradiation Model' (BIRRMDL) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'.

Error Message: Missing PCTBMNIR Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'
Description: 'Percent Bone Marrow Not Irradiated' (PCTBMNIR) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'.

Error Message: Missing RNTINJRM Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'
Description: 'Rad/Nuc Targeted Injury Model' (RNTINJRM) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'.

Error Message: Missing EORNINJR Challenge Agent Parameter when ACPARMCD = 'CAGTCAT' and ACVAL = 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'
Description: 'Exp Onset of Rad/Nuc Targeted Injury' (EORNINJR) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'.

Description: 'Combined Injury (Rad and Non-Rad) Ind' (CIRNRIND) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'.

Description: 'Irradiation Field Orientation/Sequence' (IRORSEQ) record is expected in the Challenge Agent Characterization (AC) domain when the Parameter Value (ACVAL) for the 'Challenge Agent Category' (CAGTCAT) parameter is 'RADIOLOGICAL/NUCLEAR'.

Error Message: Multiple BASELINE records for the same test
Description: By its definition clinical baseline flags (e.g., last non-missing value prior to first dose) should have only a single record for the same test for subject. Therefore, each subject (USUBJID) should have no more than one record with Baseline Flag (--BLFL) equals 'Y' for the same assessment which is defined by Test (--TESTCD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Method (--METHOD), Specimen (--SPEC), Location (--LOC), Laterality (--LAT) and Directionality (--DIR).

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --DECOD within --TERM
Description: MedDRA coding Preferred Term (--DECOD) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --HLT within --TERM
Description: MedDRA coding High Level Term (--HLT) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --HLGT within --TERM
Description: MedDRA coding High Level Group Term (--HLGT) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --BODSYS within --TERM
Description: Body System (--BODSYS) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --SOC within --TERM
Description: MedDRA System Organ Class (--SOC) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)

Error Message: Multiple --LOBXFL records for the same test
Description: By its definition Last Observation Before Exposure Flag (--LOBXFL) should have only a single record for the same test for subject. Therefore, each subject (USUBJID) should have no more than one record with  Last Observation Before Exposure Flag (--LOBXFL) equals 'Y' for the same assessment which is defined by Test (--TESTCD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Position of Subject During Observation (--POS), Method (--METHOD), Specimen (--SPEC), Location (--LOC) and Laterality (--LAT).

Error Message: Exposure start date is after the latest Disposition date
Description: Start Date/Time of Treatment (EXSTDTC) should be less than or equal to the Start Date/Time of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDTC).

Error Message: --STRESN is populated when --STRESC value is not numeric
Description: Standardized Result in Numeric Format (--STRESN) variable value should be null when Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value does not represent a numeric value, (e.g. 'BLQ', value contains '<' or '>', etc.).

Error Message: Missing values for one or more variables subject to MedDRA: --LLT, --LLTCD, --DECOD, --PTCD, --HLT, --HLTCD, --HLGT, --HLGTCD, --BODSYS, --BDSYCD, --SOC, --SOCCD
Description: Reported Term for the Adverse Event (AETERM) is expected to be coded using the Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Affairs (MedDRA). Sponsors should code each term to the MedDRA-specified hierarchy of terms. These terms/codes are represented in SDTM variables that are subject to MedDRA: AELLT, AELLTCD, AEDECOD, AEPTCD, AEHLT, AEHLTCD, AEHLGT, AEHLGTCD, AEBODSYS, AEBDSYCD, AESOC, AESOCCD.

Error Message: Missing --ENINT variable, when --STINT variable is present
Description: Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) variable must be included in the domain, when Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) variable is present.

Error Message: Missing --STINT variable, when --ENINT variable is present
Description: Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) variable must be included in the domain, when Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) variable is present.

Error Message: Negative value for --VAMT
Description: Non-missing Treatment Vehicle Amount (--VAMT) value must be greater than or equal to 0.

Error Message: Duplicate value for --SEQ variable
Description: The value of Sequence Number (DISEQ) variable must be unique for each record within a domain and within each Sponsor Device Identifier (SPDEVID)

Error Message: Invalid value for ACTARMCD
Description: The value of Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) should be no more than 20 characters in length.

Error Message: Invalid value for ACTARMCD
Description: Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening ('SCRNFAIL'),  or were not fully assigned to an Arm ('NOTASSGN'),  or randomized but not treated ('NOTTRT'), or received non-planned treatment ('UNPLAN').

Error Message: Invalid value for ACTARM
Description: Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening ('Screen Failure'), or were not fully assigned to an Arm ('Not Assigned'), or randomized, but not treated ('Not Treated') or received non-planned treatment ('Unplanned Treatment').

Error Message: Missing value for DTHFL, when DTHDTC is populated
Description: Subject Death Flag (DTHFL) value must equal 'Y', when Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) is provided.

Error Message: Missing value for DTHDTC, when DTHFL is populated
Description: Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) should be provided, when subject died (DTHFL=Y).

Error Message: Unexpected MedDRA coding in the SUPPQUAL domain
Description: MedDRA coding info should be populated using variables in the Events General Observation Class, but not in SUPPQUAL domains.

Error Message: Value for --PTCD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for Preferred Term Code (--PTCD) variable must be populated using a Preferred Term Code of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml.

Error Message: Value for --LLT not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for Lowest Level Term (--LLT) variable must be populated using a Lowest Level Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Error Message: Value for --LLT is in incorrect case

Error Message: SEND Expected variable not found
Description: Variables described in SEND IG as Expected should be included in the dataset.

Error Message: SEND/dataset variable label mismatch
Description: Variable Label in the dataset should match the variable label described in SEND IG. When creating a new domain Variable Labels could be adjusted as appropriate to properly convey the meaning in the context of the data being submitted.

Error Message: TFDETECT is after DSSTDY

Error Message: Variable which can be used only in SDTM

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --TPT within --TPTNUM, --DY, --CAT and/or --SCAT

Uniqueness for these time points is determined by a combination of the domain, study day, and, if present, category and/or subcategory (--CAT/--SCAT).

Error Message: Inconsistent value for --TPTNUM within --TPT, --DY, --CAT and/or --SCAT
